'''Javier Gerardo Milei'''{{efn|{{IPA|es|xaˈβjeɾ xeˈɾaɾðo miˈlej|-|Javier Milei - nombre (ES-ar).ogg}}}} (born 22 October 1970) is an Argentine economist and politician who has served as [[President of Argentina]] since 2023. He has taught university courses and written on various aspects of economics and politics and also hosted radio programs on the subject. [[Political positions of Javier Milei|Milei's views]] distinguish him within mainstream [[Politics of Argentina|Argentine politics]].

In November 2021, Milei was elected to the [[Argentine Chamber of Deputies]], representing the [[Buenos Aires|City of Buenos Aires]] for [[La Libertad Avanza]]. As a national deputy, he limited his legislative activities to voting, focusing instead on critiquing what he sees as Argentina's political elite and its propensity for high government spending. Milei pledged not to raise taxes and donated his national deputy salary through a monthly raffle. He defeated the incumbent economy minister, [[Sergio Massa]], in the second round of the [[2023 Argentine general election|2023 general election]], for the post of president, on a platform that held the ideological dominance of [[Peronism]] responsible for the ongoing [[2018–present Argentine monetary crisis|Argentine monetary crisis]].

Milei is known for his flamboyant personality, distinctive personal style, and strong media presence, including his catchphrase "''[[¡Viva la libertad, carajo!]]''".{{Efn|Translated into English as "Long live freedom, damn it!".|name=VVLC}} He has been described politically as a [[Right-wing populism|right-wing populist]] and [[Right-libertarianism|right-wing libertarian]] who supports ''[[laissez-faire]]'' economics, aligning specifically with [[Night-watchman state|minarchist]] and [[Anarcho-capitalism|anarcho-capitalist]] principles. Milei has proposed a comprehensive overhaul of the country's fiscal and structural policies. On social issues, he opposes [[Abortion in Argentina|abortion]] and [[Legality of euthanasia#Argentina|euthanasia]] and supports civilian ownership of [[Overview of gun laws by nation#Argentina|firearms]]. He also supports [[freedom of choice]] on drug policy, [[Prostitution in Argentina|sex work]], and [[Same-sex marriage in Argentina|same-sex marriage]]. In foreign policy, he advocates closer relations with the [[Argentina–United States relations|United States]], the [[Argentina–United Kingdom relations|United Kingdom]], and [[Argentina–Israel relations|Israel]], and supporting [[Argentina–Ukraine relations|Ukraine]] in response to the [[Russian invasion of Ukraine|Russian invasion of the country]].

==Early life and education==
Javier Gerardo Milei was born on 22 October 1970 in [[Palermo, Buenos Aires]], to Norberto Milei and Alicia Lucich.<ref name="Il Post 2023">{{cite web |date=14 August 2023 |title=Javier Milei, il leader di estrema destra che ha vinto le primarie in Argentina |url=https://www.ilpost.it/2023/08/14/chi-e-javier-milei-il-leader-di-estrema-destra-che-ha-vinto-le-primarie-in-argentina |access-date=23 August 2023 |website=Il Post |language=it |archive-date=16 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230816173456/https://www.ilpost.it/2023/08/14/chi-e-javier-milei-il-leader-di-estrema-destra-che-ha-vinto-le-primarie-in-argentina/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=21 November 2023 |title=The making of a president – Javier Milei's life before politics |url=https://www.batimes.com.ar/news/argentina/the-making-of-a-president-javier-mileis-life-before-politics.phtml |work=Buenos Aires Times |access-date=21 November 2023 |archive-date=22 November 2023 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20231122193710/https://www.batimes.com.ar/news/argentina/the-making-of-a-president-javier-mileis-life-before-politics.phtml |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Caballero |first=Joaquín |date=2023-11-21 |title=¿Quién es Karina Milei, "El Jefe" de la exitosa campaña presidencial de Javier Milei? |url=https://cnnespanol.cnn.com/2023/11/21/karina-milei-quien-es-el-jefe-orix/ |access-date=2024-09-11 |website=CNN |language=es}}</ref> He grew up in the neighborhood of [[Villa Devoto]] and later moved to the [[Sáenz Peña, Buenos Aires|Sáenz Peña]] district.<ref name="Viriglio 2023">{{cite news |last=Viriglio |first=Veronique |date=16 August 2023 |url=https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2023-08-16/argentina-milei-outsider-contro-kirchnerismo-22630111 |title=Il 'Trump argentino' che sfida Kirchner |trans-title=The "Argentine Trump" who challenges Kirchner |language=it |agency=AGI |access-date=18 August 2023 |archive-date=18 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230818050757/https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2023-08-16/argentina-milei-outsider-contro-kirchnerismo-22630111/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Alicia worked as a [[Homemaking|homemaker]],<ref name="Criales 2023">{{cite web |last=Criales |first=José Pablo |date=14 August 2023 |title=Javier Milei: The ultra-right libertarian and 'anarcho-capitalist' who represents angry Argentina |url=https://english.elpais.com/international/2023-08-14/javier-milei-the-ultra-right-libertarian-and-anarcho-capitalist-who-represents-angry-argentina.html |url-status=live |access-date=16 August 2023 |website=El País English |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230815185618/https://english.elpais.com/international/2023-08-14/javier-milei-the-ultra-right-libertarian-and-anarcho-capitalist-who-represents-angry-argentina.html |archive-date=15 August 2023}}</ref> and Norberto was a [[bus driver]]<ref name="Compte 2018">{{cite news |last=Compte |first=Juan Manuel |date=27 November 2017 |url=https://www.cronista.com/clase/dixit/Milei-La-Argentina-cree-que-Macri-es-liberal-20171127-0001.html |title=Milei: 'La Argentina cree que Macri es liberal' |work=El Cronista |language=es |access-date=15 August 2023 |archive-date=14 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230814233724/https://www.cronista.com/clase/dixit/Milei-La-Argentina-cree-que-Macri-es-liberal-20171127-0001.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Salomé |first=René |date=22 July 2023 |title=Un padre violento, una 'misión encomendada por Dios' y una traición a los suyos: el fenómeno Milei por dentro |url=https://www.infobae.com/leamos/2023/07/23/un-padre-violento-una-mision-encomendada-por-dios-y-una-traicion-a-los-suyos-el-fenomeno-milei-por-dentro |access-date=25 August 2023 |website=Infobae |language=es |archive-date=25 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230825203826/https://www.infobae.com/leamos/2023/07/23/un-padre-violento-una-mision-encomendada-por-dios-y-una-traicion-a-los-suyos-el-fenomeno-milei-por-dentro/ |url-status=live}}</ref> who later became a successful [[Businessperson|businessman]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Norberto Milei: The unknown story of the President's father {{!}} Buenos Aires Times |url=https://www.batimes.com.ar/news/opinion-and-analysis/norberto-milei-the-unknown-story-of-the-presidents-father.phtml |work=www.batimes.com.ar}}</ref>

Milei is of paternal [[Italian Argentines|Italian descent]], tracing his heritage between the municipalities of [[Cosenza]] and [[Rossano]] in the [[Calabria]] region of [[Southern Italy]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Rome |first=Wanted in |date=2024-12-13 |title=Argentina's Milei awarded Italian citizenship in Rome |url=https://www.wantedinrome.com/news/milei-awarded-italian-citizenship-in-rome.html |access-date=2024-12-16 |website=Wanted in Rome |language=en}}</ref> His paternal grandfather, Francesco "Ciccio" Milei, migrated to Argentina from Calabria in 1926.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-12-14 |title=Desde Italia, Javier Milei volvió a defender su gestión: "Creían que íbamos a durar tan solo un par de meses" |url=https://www.infobae.com/politica/2024/12/14/desde-italia-javier-milei-volvio-a-defender-su-gestion-creian-que-ibamos-a-durar-tan-solo-un-par-de-meses/ |access-date=2024-12-16 |website=infobae |language=es-ES}}</ref> On his maternal side, he is of [[Croatian Argentines|Croatian]] and Italian descent; his mother's Italian ancestors came from the municipality of [[San Severino Marche|San Severino]] in the [[Marche]] region of [[Central Italy|Central Italy.]]<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-12-19 |title=Messi and Milei: the common origins between the star and the Argentine president|url=https://italianismo.com.br/en/messi-e-milei-a-origem-em-comum-entre-o-craque-e-o-presidente-argentino/ |access-date=2024-12-19 |website=italianismo}}</ref> Through his Croatian maternal grandfather, Nicolás Mariano Lucich Bosikovic, he is related to [[Uruguay|Uruguayan]] television presenter {{ill|Rodrigo Lussich|es}}, who stated their ancestors [[Immigration to Argentina|migrated]] from [[Croatia]] and settled throughout Argentina and [[Croatian Uruguayans|Uruguay]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=22 November 2023 |title=Rodrigo Lussich reveló qué lazo familiar lo une a Javier Milei y sorprendió a todos |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/espectaculos/rodrigo-lussich-sorprendio-a-todos-y-revelo-el-lazo-familiar-que-lo-une-con-javier-milei-nid20112023/ |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=La Nación |language=es |archive-date=30 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231130222226/https://www.lanacion.com.ar/espectaculos/rodrigo-lussich-sorprendio-a-todos-y-revelo-el-lazo-familiar-que-lo-une-con-javier-milei-nid20112023/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

Furthermore, Milei revealed in 2024 that his grandfather, who had a great influence in his life, discovered that he was [[History of the Jews in Argentina|Jewish]] of [[Matrilineality in Judaism|matrilineal descent]]. His maternal grandfather had been a [[rabbi]] shortly before his death.<ref>{{cite news |date=11 April 2024 |title=Milei reveals family Jewish link as he visits US for meeting with Musk|url=https://www.batimes.com.ar/news/argentina/milei-reveals-family-jewish-link-as-he-visits-us-for-meeting-with-musk.phtml |work=Buenos Aires Times |access-date=11 April 2024}}</ref> His parents, according to Milei, [[Child abuse|beat and verbally abused him]],<ref name="Pasquini 2023">{{cite news |last=Pasquini |first=Gabriel |date=16 August 2023 |title=<!--Opinion |-->Argentina's angry polarization is a warning for the United States |newspaper=The Washington Post |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/2023/08/16/milei-argentina-polarization-politics-america |url-status=live |access-date=18 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230818163828/https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/2023/08/16/milei-argentina-polarization-politics-america |archive-date=18 August 2023 |issn=0190-8286}}</ref> causing him to not speak to them for a decade;<ref name="Criales 2023" /> he regarded them as dead.<ref>{{cite web |date=7 July 2018 |title=La insólita vida privada y familiar de Milei, el economista más polémico |url=https://www.perfil.com/noticias/protagonistas/la-insolita-vida-privada-y-familiar-de-milei-el-economista-mas-polemico.phtml |access-date=15 August 2023 |website=Perfil |language=es |archive-date=17 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317121113/https://www.perfil.com/noticias/protagonistas/la-insolita-vida-privada-y-familiar-de-milei-el-economista-mas-polemico.phtml |url-status=live}}</ref> He was supported by his maternal grandmother and his younger sister [[Karina Milei|Karina]],<ref name="Il Post 2023" /> with whom he shares a close bond with<ref>{{cite web |date=14 August 2023 |title=Karina Milei, la estratega detrás del candidato que rompió con los pronósticos en Argentina |url=https://www.emol.com/noticias/Internacional/2023/08/14/1104093/perfil-karina-milei-argentina.html |access-date=20 August 2023 |website=Emol |language=es |archive-date=20 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230820080951/https://www.emol.com/noticias/Internacional/2023/08/14/1104093/perfil-karina-milei-argentina.html |url-status=live}}</ref> and whom he calls "the boss".<ref>{{cite web |last=Alconada Mon |first=Hugo |date=16 November 2023 |title=Quién es Javier Milei {{!}} El candidato místico obsesionado con el dólar |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/politica/javier-milei-el-candidato-mistico-obsesionado-con-el-dolar-nid07082023/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231211225207/https://www.lanacion.com.ar/politica/javier-milei-el-candidato-mistico-obsesionado-con-el-dolar-nid07082023/ |archive-date=11 December 2023 |access-date=11 December 2023 |website=La Nación |language=es}}</ref>

Javier Milei attended [[Catholic school]]s,<ref name="Il Post 2023"/> including the secondary school Cardenal Copello.<ref name="Viriglio 2023"/> At school, he was nicknamed ''el Loco'' ("the madman") for his outbursts and aggressive rhetoric.<ref name="Il Post 2023"/> In his late teens and early adulthood, Milei sang in the [[cover band]] Everest, which mostly played [[Rolling Stones]] covers. He also played [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for the [[Chacarita Juniors]] football team until 1989,<ref name="Compte 2018"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://aquichacarita.wordpress.com/2017/01/15/curiosidadesun-gran-economista-fue-arquero-de-chaca-en-la-decada-del-80javier-milei |url-status=dead |title=Curiosidades: un gran economista fue arquero de Chaca en la década del 80: Javier Milei |website=Aqui Chacarita |language=es |date=15 January 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200807050518/https://aquichacarita.wordpress.com/2017/01/15/curiosidadesun-gran-economista-fue-arquero-de-chaca-en-la-decada-del-80javier-milei |archive-date=7 August 2020 |access-date=18 February 2018}}</ref> when Argentina suffered from [[hyperinflation]], and he committed to a career in economics.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.perfil.com/noticias/protagonistas/la-insolita-vida-privada-y-familiar-de-milei-el-economista-mas-polemico.phtml |title=La insólita vida privada y familiar de Milei, el economista más polémico |website=Perfil |language=es |date=7 July 2018 |access-date=17 August 2023 |archive-date=1 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230501193953/https://www.perfil.com/noticias/amp/protagonistas/la-insolita-vida-privada-y-familiar-de-milei-el-economista-mas-polemico.phtml |url-status=live}}</ref>

The collapse of [[Argentina's exchange rate]] led to Milei becoming interested in economics during the early 1980s.<ref name="Viriglio 2023"/><ref name="Compte 2018"/> Milei studied introductory economics and the law of [[supply and demand]], which he thought seemed at odds with the ongoing hyperinflation; he said he saw people throwing "themselves on top of the merchandise" in a supermarket and began to study economics in more detail to understand it.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ole.com.ar/fuera-de-juego/javier-milei-mirtha-legrand-arquero-chacarita-futbol_0_qylEjqODWA.html |title=Javier Milei contó el motivo por el cual se retiró del fútbol |trans-title=Javier Milei explained the reason why he retired from football |language=Spanish |author= |date=8 October 2023 |publisher=Ole |access-date=6 October 2023 |archive-date=9 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231009113930/https://www.ole.com.ar/fuera-de-juego/javier-milei-mirtha-legrand-arquero-chacarita-futbol_0_qylEjqODWA.html |url-status=live}}</ref> Milei obtained an economics degree (''[[Licentiate in Argentina|licentiate]]'') from the private [[University of Belgrano]] and two master's degrees from the {{ill|Instituto de Desarrollo Económico y Social|es|Instituto de Desarrollo Económico y Social}} and the private [[Torcuato di Tella University]].<ref name="Viriglio 2023"/>

==Economics career==
For over 20 years,{{when|date=January 2024}}<!-- Which years? Viriglio source does not say; WEF 2016 source says it was already over 20 years by 2016--> Milei was a professor of macroeconomics,{{clarify|at what university?|date=November 2024}} the economics of growth, microeconomics, and mathematics for economists.<ref name="Viriglio 2023" /> He specializes in [[economic growth]] and has taught several economic subjects in Argentine universities and abroad. He had written more than 50 academic papers by 2016.<ref name="WEF 2016" /><ref>{{cite news |title=¿Quién es Javier Milei? |url=https://www.agesor.com.uy/noticia.php?id=37563 |date=17 December 2018 |access-date=2 September 2023 |work=Agesor |language=es |archive-date=2 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230902163204/https://www.agesor.com.uy/noticia.php?id=37563 |url-status=live}}</ref>

By 2016, Milei had been the chief economist at Máxima AFJP, a private pension company; a head economist at Estudio Broda, a financial advising company; head economist of Corporación América; and a government consultant at the [[International Centre for Settlement of Investment Disputes]].<ref name="WEF 2016">{{cite web |url=https://www.weforum.org/people/javier-gerardo-milei |title=Javier Gerardo Milei |publisher=World Economic Forum |date=2016 |access-date=19 January 2024 |archive-date=3 May 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160503110411/https://www.weforum.org/people/javier-gerardo-milei |url-status=live}}</ref> He was also a senior economist at [[HSBC]] Argentina.<ref name="WEF 2016" /> He served as chief economist at several national and international government public bodies.<ref name="Viriglio 2023"/> Since 2012, Milei has led the Economic Studies division at Fundación Acordar, a national think tank.<ref name="WEF 2016" /> He is also a member of the [[B20 summits|B20]] and a member of the Economic Policy Group of the [[International Chamber of Commerce]], an advisor to the [[G20]]. For 15 years,{{when|date=January 2024}} he worked at the private company Corporación América as the chief economist and financial adviser to [[Eduardo Eurnekian]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=30 June 2023 |title=Milei ante el círculo rojo: se reencontró con su exjefe y despertó risas, pero no confianza en su plan |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/economia/milei-ante-el-circulo-rojo-se-reencontro-con-su-exjefe-y-desperto-risas-pero-no-confianza-en-su-plan-nid29062023 |access-date=24 July 2023 |website=La Nación |language=es |archive-date=24 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230724051250/https://www.lanacion.com.ar/economia/milei-ante-el-circulo-rojo-se-reencontro-con-su-exjefe-y-desperto-risas-pero-no-confianza-en-su-plan-nid29062023/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

Milei is the author of several books,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.cronista.com/autor/jmilei<!--https://www.cronista.com/columnista/jmilei--> |url-status=dead |title=Perfil de Javier Milei |work=El Cronista |language=es |date=2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170208054457/https://www.cronista.com/columnista/jmilei |archive-date=8 February 2017 |access-date=15 August 2023}}</ref> including ''[[El camino del libertario]]''.<ref name="Chavez 2022">{{cite web |last=Chavez |first=Facundo |date=4 March 2022 |url=https://www.infobae.com/reportajes/2022/03/04/javier-milei-presento-el-camino-del-libertario-y-aseguro-es-el-libro-de-un-candidato-a-presidente |title=Javier Milei presentó 'El camino del libertario' y aseguró: 'Es el libro de un candidato a presidente' |language=es |website=Infobae |access-date=16 August 2023 |archive-date=16 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230816203339/https://www.infobae.com/reportajes/2022/03/04/javier-milei-presento-el-camino-del-libertario-y-aseguro-es-el-libro-de-un-candidato-a-presidente/ |url-status=live}}</ref> He has a notable presence on television, with a 2018 ranking by Ejes showing him as the most interviewed economist on TV, at 235 interviews and 193,347 seconds.<ref>{{cite web |date=27 September 2018 |title=Milei encabeza el ranking de los economistas con más segundos al aire |url=https://www.expedientepolitico.com.ar/milei-encabeza-el-ranking-de-los-economistas-con-mas-seguros-al-aire |access-date=20 August 2023 |website=Expediente Político |language=es |archive-date=20 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231120002233/https://www.expedientepolitico.com.ar/milei-encabeza-el-ranking-de-los-economistas-con-mas-seguros-al-aire/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Milei also hosted his own radio show, ''Demoliendo mitos'' (''Demolishing Myths''),<ref>{{cite web |date=18 November 2018 |title=Javier Milei explotó por los proyectos más 'inútiles' de los legisladores y el video se volvió viral |url=https://www.infobae.com/politica/2018/11/18/javier-milei-exploto-por-los-proyectos-mas-raros-de-los-legisladores-y-el-video-se-volvio-viral |access-date=20 August 2023 |website=Infobae |language=es |archive-date=25 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230425053307/https://www.infobae.com/politica/2018/11/18/javier-milei-exploto-por-los-proyectos-mas-raros-de-los-legisladores-y-el-video-se-volvio-viral/ |url-status=live}}</ref> featuring regular appearances by [[Juan Bautista Alberdi|Alberdian]] and [[right-wing libertarian]] personalities, including the economist and businessman Gustavo Lazzari, the lawyer Pablo Torres Barthe, and the political scientist María Zaldívar.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.conexionabierta.com.ar/programas/demoliendo-mitos.html |title=Demoliendo mitos |website=Radio Conexión Abierta |language=es |date=2017 |access-date=15 August 2023 |archive-date=9 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230409222813/https://www.conexionabierta.com.ar/programas/demoliendo-mitos.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=XPHqzVFaDQw |title='Demoliendo mitos', de J.Milei con G.Lazzari, D.Giacomini, y N.Márquez – 09/02/18 |website=Radio Conexión Abierta |language=es |date=9 February 2018 |access-date=15 August 2023 |via=YouTube |archive-date=14 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230814104717/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XPHqzVFaDQw |url-status=live}}</ref>

==Early political career==
===Rise to prominence===
[[File:Javier Milei en una entrevista de TN.png|thumb|Milei during an interview on ''[[Todo Noticias]]'' in 2019|left]]
During the 2010s, Milei achieved significant notoriety and public exposure in debates featured on Argentine television programs characterized by insults to his rivals,<ref>{{cite web |date=27 August 2021 |title=El insulto de Javier Milei a Rodríguez Larreta: 'Zurdo de mierda, te puedo aplastar' |url=https://www.infobae.com/politica/2021/08/28/el-insulto-de-javier-milei-a-rodriguez-larreta-zurdo-de-mierda-te-puedo-aplastar |access-date=30 August 2023 |website=Infobae |language=es |archive-date=26 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230426021739/https://www.infobae.com/politica/2021/08/28/el-insulto-de-javier-milei-a-rodriguez-larreta-zurdo-de-mierda-te-puedo-aplastar/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=17 January 2022 |title=El increíble ranking de insultos de Javier Milei |url=https://www.perfil.com/noticias/politica/el-increible-ranking-de-insultos-de-javier-milei.phtml |access-date=30 August 2023 |website=Perfil |language=es |archive-date=29 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230929145520/https://www.perfil.com/noticias/politica/el-increible-ranking-de-insultos-de-javier-milei.phtml |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Nicas |first=Jack |date=20 October 2023 |title=Javier Milei, a 'Mini-Trump,' Could Be Argentina's Next President |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2023/10/20/world/americas/javier-milei-argentina-election.html |access-date=28 November 2023 |issn=1553-8095 |archive-date=28 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231128043055/https://www.nytimes.com/2023/10/20/world/americas/javier-milei-argentina-election.html |url-status=live}}</ref> foul language,<ref>{{cite web |date=27 June 2018 |title=Javier Milei maltrató a una periodista en una conferencia de prensa: Sos una burra |url=https://www.primerafuente.com.ar/noticias/75458/javier-milei-maltrato-periodista-conferencia-prensa-sos-burra |access-date=30 August 2023 |website=Primera Fuente |language=es |archive-date=30 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230830192922/https://www.primerafuente.com.ar/noticias/75458/javier-milei-maltrato-periodista-conferencia-prensa-sos-burra |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=27 January 2021 |title=Milei insultó a Kulfas en medio de una entrevista: '¡Para vos, pedazo de mierda!' |url=https://www.iprofesional.com/economia/308167-video-de-insultos-de-milei-contra-kulfas-y-guzman-les-dijo-pelotudo-e-inutil |access-date=30 August 2023 |website=iProfesional |language=es |archive-date=25 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230425053313/https://www.iprofesional.com/economia/308167-video-de-insultos-de-milei-contra-kulfas-y-guzman-les-dijo-pelotudo-e-inutil |url-status=live}}</ref> and aggressive rhetoric when expressing and debating his ideals and beliefs,<ref>{{cite web |date=22 August 2021 |title=La Ciudad de la furia libertaria |url=https://www.letrap.com.ar/nota/2021-8-22-10-6-0-la-ciudad-de-la-furia-libertaria |access-date=30 August 2023 |website=LetraP |language=es |archive-date=21 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230421225625/https://www.letrap.com.ar/nota/2021-8-22-10-6-0-la-ciudad-de-la-furia-libertaria |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=González |first=Juan Luis |date=5 September 2021 |title=Javier Milei y el peligroso éxito de la antipolítica |url=https://noticias.perfil.com/noticias/politica/javier-milei-radiografia-del-peligroso-exito-de-la-antipolitica.phtml |access-date=30 August 2023 |website=Revista Noticias |language=es |archive-date=15 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230815135944/https://noticias.perfil.com/noticias/politica/javier-milei-radiografia-del-peligroso-exito-de-la-antipolitica.phtml |url-status=live}}</ref> such as one with Buenos Aires chief of government [[Horacio Rodríguez Larreta]].<ref>{{cite web |date=27 August 2021 |title=Javier Milei insultó a Horacio Rodríguez Larreta y lo amenazó: 'Zurdo de mierda, te puedo aplastar' |url=https://www.clarin.com/politica/javier-milei-insulto-horacio-rodriguez-larreta-amenazo-zurdo-mierda-puedo-aplastar-_0_rLUZy3FZq.html |access-date=30 August 2023 |website=Clarín |language=es |archive-date=25 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230425053311/https://www.clarin.com/politica/javier-milei-insulto-horacio-rodriguez-larreta-amenazo-zurdo-mierda-puedo-aplastar-_0_rLUZy3FZq.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=22 March 2023 |title=Javier Milei se cruzó con una periodista y lo acusan de 'maltrato y agresiones' |url=https://www.clarin.com/politica/javier-milei-cruzo-periodista-acusan-maltrato-agresiones-_0_Y0DDR04KDU.html |access-date=30 August 2023 |website=Clarín |language=es |archive-date=1 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230401015205/https://www.clarin.com/politica/javier-milei-cruzo-periodista-acusan-maltrato-agresiones-_0_Y0DDR04KDU.html |url-status=live}}</ref> This led many commentators to label him antipolitical or disruptive.<ref name="BBC News Mundo 2023">{{cite web |date=14 August 2023 |title=Quién es Javier Milei y cuáles son las radicales propuestas con las que ganó las primarias en Argentina |url=https://www.bbc.com/mundo/articles/c7202q20g27o |access-date=30 August 2023 |website=BBC News Mundo |language=es |archive-date=29 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230829153736/https://www.bbc.com/mundo/articles/c7202q20g27o |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Ted Cruz]], a United States senator, shared an interview between [[Viviana Canosa]] and Milei on Twitter, jokingly proposing to invite him to the [[2024 Republican Party presidential debates]].<ref name="Infobae 2023">{{cite web |date=19 August 2023 |title=Un líder republicano de EEUU mencionó a Javier Milei y pidió que se lo incluya en el debate presidencial de su partido |url=https://www.infobae.com/politica/2023/08/19/un-lider-republicano-de-eeuu-menciono-a-javier-milei-y-pidio-que-se-lo-incluya-en-el-debate-presidencial-de-su-partido |access-date=30 August 2023 |website=Infobae |language=es |archive-date=30 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230830175625/https://www.infobae.com/politica/2023/08/19/un-lider-republicano-de-eeuu-menciono-a-javier-milei-y-pidio-que-se-lo-incluya-en-el-debate-presidencial-de-su-partido/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

In February 2017, Milei considered [[Domingo Cavallo]] the best minister of the economy of Argentina because he ended the 1989 hyperinflation and started reforms in the state. He blamed the 2001 crisis on the mistakes of the previous ministers of the economy that Cavallo could not fix in time.<ref>{{cite news |last=Del Rio |first=José |date=2 February 2017 |title=Javier Milei: 'Quien más ha hecho por la economía argentina fue Cavallo' |language=es |work=La Nación |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/economia/javier-milei-quien-mas-ha-hecho-por-la-economia-argentina-fue-cavallo-nid1981193 |url-status=dead |access-date=14 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210211050556/https://www.lanacion.com.ar/economia/javier-milei-quien-mas-ha-hecho-por-la-economia-argentina-fue-cavallo-nid1981193 |archive-date=11 February 2021}}</ref> In November 2017, he caused a stir by declaring that "the main producer of Argentina's economists is a Marxist indoctrination center", referring to the [[Faculty of Economic Sciences, University of Buenos Aires]], leading to what he called "the ubiquitous proliferation of [[Keynesian]] brutes".<ref>{{cite web |last=Compte |first=Juan Manuel |date=27 November 2017 |title=Milei, entre la solidez técnica y la aspereza de un exarquero de Chacarita |url=https://www.cronista.com//dixit/Milei-La-Argentina-cree-que-Macri-es-liberal-20171127-0001.html |access-date=14 August 2023 |website=Cronista |language=es |archive-date=5 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230505024834/https://www.cronista.com//dixit/Milei-La-Argentina-cree-que-Macri-es-liberal-20171127-0001.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 26 June 2018, Milei called journalist Teresita Frías a ''burro'' (literally "donkey", meaning "ignorant" or "uneducated" in Argentine slang) after she criticized his ideological views as totalitarian.<ref>{{cite web |date=28 June 2018 |title=Escándalo en Salta: el economista Javier Milei maltrató y llamó 'burra' a una periodista |url=https://www.clarin.com/espectaculos/fama/escandalo-salta-economista-javier-milei-maltrato-llamo-burra-periodista_0_BylaYFffm.html |access-date=14 August 2023 |website=Clarín |language=es |archive-date=27 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230327021033/https://www.clarin.com/espectaculos/fama/escandalo-salta-economista-javier-milei-maltrato-llamo-burra-periodista_0_BylaYFffm.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=28 June 2018 |title=El economista Javier Milei maltrató a una periodista en Salta: 'Sos una burra' |url=https://www.infobae.com/sociedad/2018/06/28/el-economista-javier-milei-maltrato-a-una-periodista-en-salta-sos-una-burra |access-date=14 August 2023 |website=infobae |language=es |archive-date=27 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230327021053/https://www.infobae.com/sociedad/2018/06/28/el-economista-javier-milei-maltrato-a-una-periodista-en-salta-sos-una-burra/ |url-status=live}}</ref> As he refused to apologize, Milei was accused of exerting gender violence, and a local court mandated a psychological examination. Family and Gender judge Carmelo Paz forbade him from participating in public gatherings as a panelist or lecturer within the boundaries of the city of [[San José de Metán|Metán]], under the threat of legal action.<ref>{{cite news |date=11 July 2018 |title=Violencia de género: Milei se presentó hoy en Metán junto al abogado Marcelo Arancibia |work=El Tribuno |url=https://www.eltribuno.com/salta/nota/2018-7-11-10-16-0-violencia-de-genero-milei-se-presento-hoy-en-metan-junto-al-abogado-marcelo-arancibia |url-status=dead |access-date=14 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230327021033/https://www.eltribuno.com/salta/nota/2018-7-11-10-16-0-violencia-de-genero-milei-se-presento-hoy-en-metan-junto-al-abogado-marcelo-arancibia |archive-date=27 March 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=12 July 2018 |title=Ordenan una pericia psicológica para el economista Javier Milei |url=https://www.perfil.com/noticias/sociedad/ordenan-una-pericia-psicologica-para-el-economista-javier-milei.phtml |access-date=14 August 2023 |website=Perfil |language=es |archive-date=27 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230327021038/https://www.perfil.com/noticias/sociedad/ordenan-una-pericia-psicologica-para-el-economista-javier-milei.phtml |url-status=live}}</ref> In 2018, he made his acting debut in his play ''El consultorio de Milei'' with Claudio Rico and Diego Sucalesca. In 2019, ''[[Noticias (magazine)|Noticias]]'' named him one of the most influential people in Argentina. In 2020, he spoke in favor of protests against [[Alberto Fernández]]'s government.<ref name="Viriglio 2023"/>

===2021 legislative campaign===
From 2020 to 2021, Milei was a member of [[Avanza Libertad]] (Advance, Freedom), a political party founded by [[José Luis Espert]].<ref>{{cite web |date=24 July 2023 |title=José Luis Espert y Javier Milei presentaron listas de candidatos separadas y con sorpresas |url=https://www.clarin.com/politica/jose-luis-espert-javier-milei-presentaron-listas-candidatos-separadas-sorpresas_0_em9KxhoHR.html |access-date=1 December 2023 |website=Clarín |language=es |archive-date=21 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230421045754/https://www.clarin.com/politica/jose-luis-espert-javier-milei-presentaron-listas-candidatos-separadas-sorpresas_0_em9KxhoHR.html |url-status=live}}</ref> During his campaign for the [[Argentine Chamber of Deputies]], Milei focused on Buenos Aires neighborhoods, where he took strolls and had talks with ordinary people.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pressreader.com/argentina/perfil-sabado/20210821/281668258057324 |title=Milei llega a Belgrano con su mensaje "antipolítica" |trans-title=Milei arrives to Belgrano with his "apolitical" message |language=Spanish |author= |date=21 August 2021 |publisher=Perfil |access-date=17 October 2023 |archive-date=22 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231022124732/https://www.pressreader.com/argentina/perfil-sabado/20210821/281668258057324 |url-status=live}}</ref> He pledged not to support any tax increases or new taxes.<ref name="IP Noticias 2021">{{cite web |date=21 July 2021 |title=Javier Milei: 'Antes de subir los impuestos me corto un brazo' |url=https://www.ip.digital/nota/9554-javier-milei-antes-de-subir-los-impuestos-me-corto-un-brazo |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210722030450/https://www.ip.digital/nota/9554-javier-milei-antes-de-subir-los-impuestos-me-corto-un-brazo |archive-date=22 July 2021 |url-status=live |access-date=21 July 2021 |website=IP Noticias |language=es}}</ref> He ran under the slogan "I didn't come here to lead lambs, but to awaken lions", denouncing what he saw as a political caste,<ref>{{cite web |date=14 November 2021 |title=Javier Milei, el libertario radical 'outsider' que desafiará a la 'casta política' en Argentina |url=https://milenio.com/internacional/latinoamerica/javier-milei-libertario-desafia-establishment-argentina |access-date=25 April 2023 |website=Milenio |language=es |archive-date=14 September 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210914235852/https://milenio.com/internacional/latinoamerica/javier-milei-libertario-desafia-establishment-argentina |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |access-date=9 February 2022 |date=15 November 2021 |language=es |title=La libertad avanza: el nuevo partido libertario que ha entrado en el Congreso de Argentina |url=https://www.elperiodicodearagon.com/internacional/2021/11/15/libertad-avanza-nuevo-partido-libertario-59560693.html |website=El Periódico de Aragón |archive-date=20 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220920170853/https://www.elperiodicodearagon.com/internacional/2021/11/15/libertad-avanza-nuevo-partido-libertario-59560693.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |access-date=8 October 2022 |work=La Nación |date=13 December 2021 |title=Javier Milei. Un fenómeno libertario con prédica antisistema |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/sociedad/javier-milei-un-fenomeno-libertario-con-predica-antisistema-nid13122021/ |archive-date=20 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231120002230/https://www.lanacion.com.ar/sociedad/javier-milei-un-fenomeno-libertario-con-predica-antisistema-nid13122021/ |url-status=live}}</ref> which he said was composed of "useless, parasitic politicians who have never worked".<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.lemonde.fr/international/article/2021/10/13/javier-milei-l-ultraliberal-qui-joue-les-trublions-de-la-politique-argentine_6098156_3210.html |title=Javier Milei, l'ultralibéral qui joue les trublions de la politique argentine |work=Le Monde |language=fr |date=13 October 2021 |access-date=20 August 2023 |archive-date=14 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230814223451/https://www.lemonde.fr/international/article/2021/10/13/javier-milei-l-ultraliberal-qui-joue-les-trublions-de-la-politique-argentine_6098156_3210.html |url-status=live}}</ref> He called politicians "rats" and said they form "a parasitic caste" that thinks only about getting rich.<ref name="Molina 2023">{{cite web |last=Molina |first=Federico Rivas |date=30 March 2023 |title=Javier Milei, the unclassifiable Argentine politician |url=https://english.elpais.com/international/2023-03-30/javier-milei-the-unclassifiable-argentine-politician.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230822071215/https://english.elpais.com/international/2023-03-30/javier-milei-the-unclassifiable-argentine-politician.html |archive-date=22 August 2023 |access-date=22 August 2023 |website=El País English}}</ref> He used phrases like "I'm here to kick these criminals out"<ref name="Il Post 2023"/><ref name="Alonso 2023">{{cite web |last=Alonso |first=John Francis |date=19 August 2023 |title=Javier Milei: qué es la ideología libertaria y qué tanto se adhiere a ella el candidato antisistema argentino |url=https://www.bbc.com/mundo/articles/c19l9k4j9g4o |access-date=25 August 2023 |website=BBC News Mundo |language=es |archive-date=24 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230824150846/https://www.bbc.com/mundo/articles/c19l9k4j9g4o |url-status=live}}</ref> and was especially supported by youth;<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Banerjee |first1=Somsubhra |last2=Iglesias Seifert |first2=Demian |date=4 September 2023 |title=Right-wing populism reaches Argentina |url=https://theloop.ecpr.eu/argentina-turns-to-the-populist-far-right |access-date=6 September 2023 |website=The Loop |archive-date=6 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230906145223/https://theloop.ecpr.eu/argentina-turns-to-the-populist-far-right/ |url-status=live}}</ref> he promoted his political views on television, radio, and [[YouTube]].<ref name="Viriglio 2023"/> Additionally, Milei reconciled with his parents.<ref>{{Cite web |date=18 September 2021 |title=Javier Milei: 'Mis padres son tan liberales como yo' |url=https://www.perfil.com/noticias/periodismopuro/javier-milei-mis-padres-son-tan-liberales-como-yo.phtml |access-date=28 October 2022 |website=Perfil |language=es |archive-date=20 September 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210920055345/https://www.perfil.com/noticias/periodismopuro/javier-milei-mis-padres-son-tan-liberales-como-yo.phtml |url-status=live}}</ref>

In July 2021, Milei established the coalition [[La Libertad Avanza]] (Freedom Advances),<ref>{{cite news |date=15 July 2021 |title="La Libertad Avanza", la coalición de Milei para competir en la Ciudad |work=Noticias Urbanas |url=https://www.noticiasurbanas.com.ar/noticias/la-libertad-avanza-la-coalicion-de-milei-para-competir-en-la-ciudad |access-date=21 November 2021 |language=es |archive-date=28 September 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210928011629/https://www.noticiasurbanas.com.ar/noticias/la-libertad-avanza-la-coalicion-de-milei-para-competir-en-la-ciudad/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=11 November 2021 |title=Javier Milei dialogó sobre los proyectos de La Libertad Avanza |url=https://consejo.org.ar/noticias/2021/ciclo-candidatos-diputados-milei |access-date=20 May 2022 |website=Consejo.org.ar |language=es |archive-date=1 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221001191803/https://consejo.org.ar/noticias/2021/ciclo-candidatos-diputados-milei |url-status=live}}</ref> which secured third place in [[Partisan primary|primary election]]s with 13.66 percent of the vote and third in the [[2021 Argentine legislative election]] with 17 percent,<ref>{{cite web |title=Elecciones 2021: Javier Milei con La Libertad Avanza se consolidó como la tercera fuerza en Capital Federal |url=https://www.lavoz.com.ar/politica/elecciones-2021-javier-milei-con-la-libertad-avanza-se-consolido-como-la-tercera-fuerza-en-capital-federal |access-date=20 May 2022 |website=La Voz del Interior |date=15 November 2021 |language=es |archive-date=15 November 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211115005919/https://www.lavoz.com.ar/politica/elecciones-2021-javier-milei-con-la-libertad-avanza-se-consolido-como-la-tercera-fuerza-en-capital-federal |url-status=live}}</ref> and the [[libertarian]] coalition entered the [[Argentine Congress]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Centenera |first=Mar |date=15 November 2021 |title=La ultraderecha entra en el Congreso de Argentina |url=https://elpais.com/internacional/2021-11-15/la-ultraderecha-entra-en-el-congreso-argentino.html |url-access=registration |access-date=25 April 2023 |work=El País |language=es |archive-date=20 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231120002230/https://elpais.com/internacional/2021-11-15/la-ultraderecha-entra-en-el-congreso-argentino.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="El Diario 2021">{{cite web |first1=Mayra Castillo |last1=Castrillón |first2=Nelly Luna |last2=Amancio |first3=Victoria |last3=De Masi |first4=Laura |last4=Scofield |first5=Mariama |last5=Correia y Rute Pina |first6=Kennia |last6=Velázquez |first7=Natalia |last7=Arbeláez |first8=María José |last8=Echeverry y Elisa |date=16 November 2021 |title=La ultraderecha arma nuevas alianzas para crecer en América Latina |url=https://www.eldiarioar.com/mundo/ultraderecha-arma-nuevas-alianzas-crecer-america-latina_130_8493638.html |access-date=17 August 2023 |website=elDiarioAR.com |language=es |archive-date=16 November 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211116103710/https://www.eldiarioar.com/mundo/ultraderecha-arma-nuevas-alianzas-crecer-america-latina_130_8493638.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Centenera |first=Mar |date=21 November 2021 |title=La ultraderecha irrumpe en Argentina aupada por los más jóvenes |url=https://elpais.com/internacional/2021-11-21/la-ultraderecha-irrumpe-en-argentina-aupada-por-los-mas-jovenes.html |work=El País |language=es |access-date=17 August 2023 |archive-date=20 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231120002240/https://elpais.com/internacional/2021-11-21/la-ultraderecha-irrumpe-en-argentina-aupada-por-los-mas-jovenes.html |url-status=live}}</ref> They performed best in [[Córdoba, Argentina|Córdoba]] and [[Santa Fe, Argentina|Santa Fe]], the second and third-most populated districts in the country. They performed well in [[Peronism|Peronist]] strongholds in [[Tucumán Province|North Tucumán]], [[Salta Province|Salta]], [[La Rioja Province, Argentina|La Rioja]], [[San Juan Province, Argentina|San Juan]], and [[Santa Cruz Province, Argentina|Santa Cruz]] in Patagonia, which is considered the cradle of [[Kirchnerism]].<ref name="Viriglio 2023" />

==National deputyship==
Upon assuming office as a deputy, Milei fulfilled one of his campaign promises by raffling off his salary to a random person each month, aiming to "return money to the citizens". He described this monthly raffle, which is open to anyone,<ref>{{cite web |date=14 January 2022 |title=Polémica en Argentina: el diputado ultraconservador Milei sortea públicamente su sueldo |url=https://www.france24.com/es/am%C3%A9rica-latina/20220114-javier-milei-sorteo-sueldo-diputado-argentina |access-date=28 April 2023 |website=France 24 |language=es |archive-date=14 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220114003616/https://www.france24.com/es/am%C3%A9rica-latina/20220114-javier-milei-sorteo-sueldo-diputado-argentina |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Javier Milei volvió a sortear su sueldo: cuál es la cifra y cómo anotarse |url=https://www.ambito.com/politica/javier-milei/volvio-sortear-su-sueldo-cual-es-la-cifra-y-como-anotarse-n5648938 |access-date=24 July 2023 |work=Ámbito Financiero |language=es |date=11 February 2023 |archive-date=12 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230212074054/https://www.ambito.com/politica/javier-milei/volvio-sortear-su-sueldo-cual-es-la-cifra-y-como-anotarse-n5648938 |url-status=live}}</ref> as a way to get rid of what he considered dirty money, saying: "The state is a criminal organization that finances itself through taxes levied on people by force. We are returning the money that the political caste stole."<ref name="Il Post 2023" /> His monthly raffle for his salary has given away more than seven million pesos since his parliamentary election.<ref name="Nunes 2023"/> As a national deputy, Milei had been present in the chamber 52 percent of the time as of April 2023.<ref>{{cite web |date=20 April 2023 |title=Milei en el Congreso: 48% de inasistencia a las votaciones |url=https://www.telam.com.ar/notas/202304/626166-diputados-milei-ausencias-denuncia.html |access-date=2 September 2023 |website=Télam |language=es |archive-date=2 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230902002342/https://www.telam.com.ar/notas/202304/626166-diputados-milei-ausencias-denuncia.html |url-status=live}}</ref> As of August 2023, he had not proposed any laws or joined any parliamentary commissions.<ref>{{cite web |date=12 July 2022 |title=Milei se ausentó en la mitad de las votaciones en el Congreso, no integra comisiones, ni presentó proyectos |url=https://www.perfil.com/noticias/politica/javier-milei-falto-a-una-sola-sesion-desde-que-es-diputado-pero-se-ausento-de-la-mitad-de-las-votaciones.phtml |access-date=2 September 2023 |website=Perfil |language=es |archive-date=2 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230902002343/https://www.perfil.com/noticias/politica/javier-milei-falto-a-una-sola-sesion-desde-que-es-diputado-pero-se-ausento-de-la-mitad-de-las-votaciones.phtml |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Nunes 2023">{{cite web |last=Nunes |first=Sofía |date=18 August 2023 |title=Javier Milei y su rol en el Congreso: el desempeño del diputado desde que asumió |url=https://www.iprofesional.com/politica/387178-javier-milei-cual-fue-su-desempeno-como-diputado-nacional |access-date=1 September 2023 |website=iProfesional |language=es |archive-date=2 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230902000315/https://www.iprofesional.com/politica/387178-javier-milei-cual-fue-su-desempeno-como-diputado-nacional |url-status=live}}</ref> One of his absences was particularly criticized by the [[Juntos por el Cambio]] opposition because it allowed the national government to raise taxes on plane tickets by a single vote.<ref>{{cite web |date=26 October 2022 |title=Fuertes críticas a Milei por su ausencia en la votación de un nuevo impuesto |url=https://www.perfil.com/noticias/politica/fuertes-criticas-a-milei-por-su-ausencia-en-la-votacion-de-la-creacion-de-un-nuevo-impuesto.phtml |access-date=2 September 2023 |website=Perfil |language=es |archive-date=2 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230902002344/https://www.perfil.com/noticias/politica/fuertes-criticas-a-milei-por-su-ausencia-en-la-votacion-de-la-creacion-de-un-nuevo-impuesto.phtml |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=26 October 2022 |title='La tasa Milei': el oficialismo aprobó el Impuesto a los pasajes de avión por un voto y JxC apuntó contra el libertario |url=https://www.infobae.com/politica/2022/10/26/el-oficialismo-aprobo-el-impuesto-a-los-pasajes-de-avion-por-un-solo-voto-y-jxc-apunto-contra-milei-porque-estuvo-ausente |access-date=2 September 2023 |website=Infobae |language=es |archive-date=2 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230902002343/https://www.infobae.com/politica/2022/10/26/el-oficialismo-aprobo-el-impuesto-a-los-pasajes-de-avion-por-un-solo-voto-y-jxc-apunto-contra-milei-porque-estuvo-ausente/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=26 October 2022 |title=El bloque de Javier Milei explicó por qué se ausentó de la votación que definió aplicar un nuevo impuesto a los pasajes aéreos |url=https://www.infobae.com/politica/2022/10/26/el-bloque-de-javier-milei-explico-por-que-se-ausento-de-la-votacion-que-definio-aplicar-un-nuevo-impuesto-a-los-pasajes-aereos |access-date=2 September 2023 |website=Infobae |language=es |archive-date=2 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230902002342/https://www.infobae.com/politica/2022/10/26/el-bloque-de-javier-milei-explico-por-que-se-ausento-de-la-votacion-que-definio-aplicar-un-nuevo-impuesto-a-los-pasajes-aereos/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

In July 2023, Milei faced an investigation into the alleged selling of [[Candidate|candidacies]] within La Libertad Avanza.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Centenera |first1=Mar |title=Javier Milei, Argentina's far-right populist, accused of engaging in the sale of candidacies |url=https://english.elpais.com/international/2023-07-08/javier-milei-argentinas-far-right-populist-accused-of-engaging-in-the-sale-of-candidacies.html |access-date=8 July 2023 |work=El País English |date=8 July 2023 |archive-date=8 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230708184348/https://english.elpais.com/international/2023-07-08/javier-milei-argentinas-far-right-populist-accused-of-engaging-in-the-sale-of-candidacies.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=12 July 2023 |title=Desmintieron el pago de candidaturas: 120 candidatos liberales se presentaron en la Justicia para defender a Milei |url=https://derechadiario.com.ar/argentina/desmintieron-el-pago-de-candidaturas-120-candidatos-liberales-se-presentaron-en-la-justicia-para-defender-a-milei |access-date=24 July 2023 |website=La Derecha Diario |language=es |archive-date=24 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230724053756/https://derechadiario.com.ar/argentina/desmintieron-el-pago-de-candidaturas-120-candidatos-liberales-se-presentaron-en-la-justicia-para-defender-a-milei |url-status=live}}</ref> Businessman [[Juan Carlos Blumberg]] said that the coalition "made politics a business", which prompted Milei to deny that there were paid candidates. Milei was also accused of having been funded and supported by [[Peronism]]. Journalist Juan Luis González said that Milei "allowed himself to be financed by provincial governments, received technical, logistical, and monetary aid from the Peronism that he claims to fight, threatened all those who wanted to open their mouths".<ref name="iProfesional 2023">{{cite web |date=6 July 2023 |title=Su perro muerto, esoterismo y la 'misión' de Dios: los secretos de Javier Milei |url=https://www.iprofesional.com/economia/384634-su-perro-muerto-y-la-mision-de-dios-los-secretos-de-milei |access-date=25 August 2023 |website=iProfesional |language=es |archive-date=22 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230822143731/https://www.iprofesional.com/economia/384634-su-perro-muerto-y-la-mision-de-dios-los-secretos-de-milei |url-status=live}}</ref> Statements by the prosecutor, Ramiro González, did not provide concrete data about the allegations. While the investigation was still progressing as of July 2023, Milei dismissed it as a political operation to discredit him<ref>{{cite web |last=González |first=Gustavo |date=20 August 2023 |title=¿Puede Conan gobernar la Argentina? |url=https://www.perfil.com/noticias/columnistas/puede-conan-gobernar-la-argentina-por-gustavo-gonzalez.phtml |access-date=25 August 2023 |website=Perfil |language=es |archive-date=24 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230824174102/https://www.perfil.com/noticias/columnistas/puede-conan-gobernar-la-argentina-por-gustavo-gonzalez.phtml |url-status=live}}</ref> and demanded that Ramiro González be investigated, accusing him of damaging his image.<ref>{{cite web |date=15 July 2023 |title=La Justicia no encontró pruebas sobre la venta de candidaturas de Milei y analiza llamar a más testigos |url=https://tn.com.ar/politica/2023/07/15/la-justicia-todavia-no-encontro-pruebas-sobre-la-venta-de-candidaturas-de-milei-y-llamo-a-mas-testigos |access-date=24 July 2023 |website=Todo Noticias |language=es |archive-date=15 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230715184433/https://tn.com.ar/politica/2023/07/15/la-justicia-todavia-no-encontro-pruebas-sobre-la-venta-de-candidaturas-de-milei-y-llamo-a-mas-testigos |url-status=live}}</ref> The case was closed on March 2024, as the prosecutor could not find enough evidence to make a formal accusation.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.lanacion.com.ar/politica/la-fiscalia-ordeno-el-archivo-provisorio-de-la-investigacion-por-la-supuesta-venta-de-candidaturas-nid22032024/|title= La fiscalía ordenó el "archivo provisorio" de la investigación por la supuesta venta de candidaturas en La Libertad Avanza|trans-title= The prosecutor's office ordered the "provisional archiving" of the investigation into the alleged sale of candidacies in La Libertad Avanza|language= Spanish|author= |date= March 22, 2024|publisher= La Nación|accessdate=December 10, 2024}}</ref>

==2023 Argentine general election==
===2023 presidential campaign===
{{main|Javier Milei 2023 presidential campaign}}
[[File:Javier Milei VIVA22 (3).jpg|thumb|Milei posing with Villarruel in October 2022]]
A member of the [[Libertarian Party (Argentina)|Libertarian Party]], Milei ran for [[president of Argentina]] as part of La Libertad Avanza. His running mate was [[Victoria Villarruel]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Rivas Molina |first=Federico |date=15 August 2023 |url=https://elpais.com/argentina/2023-08-15/que-tiene-javier-milei-en-la-cabeza.html |url-status=live |title=Que tiene en la cabeza Javier Milei |work=El País |language=es |issn=0307-1235 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230816194336/https://elpais.com/argentina/2023-08-15/que-tiene-javier-milei-en-la-cabeza.html |archive-date=16 August 2023 |access-date=17 August 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Nugent |first1=Ciara |last2=Stott |first2=Michael |date=26 November 2023 |title=How similar is Argentina's Javier Milei to Donald Trump and Jair Bolsonaro? |url=https://www.ft.com/content/d2c033c5-65cb-41e8-bb06-b995fc25f9c5 |access-date=28 November 2023 |website=Financial Times |archive-date=26 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231126053151/https://www.ft.com/content/d2c033c5-65cb-41e8-bb06-b995fc25f9c5 |url-status=live}}</ref> His younger sister, Karina Milei, managed his campaign.<ref name="Viriglio 2023"/> In May 2022, Milei was rising in the polls.<ref>{{cite web |last=Oque |first=Facundo |date=17 May 2022 |title=El fenómeno Javer Milei: ¿por qué crece en las encuestas? |url=https://izquierdaweb.com/javier-milei-encuestas |access-date=28 August 2023 |website=Izquierda Web |language=es |archive-date=28 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230828035039/https://izquierdaweb.com/javier-milei-encuestas/ |url-status=live}}</ref> In June 2022, he officially launched his presidential campaign.<ref>{{Cite news |date=11 June 2022 |title=Milei launches presidential bid in fiasco event attended by only a few |url=https://en.mercopress.com/2022/06/11/milei-launches-presidential-bid-in-fiasco-event-attended-by-only-a-few |work=MercoPress |access-date=28 November 2023 |archive-date=2 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231202224014/https://en.mercopress.com/2022/06/11/milei-launches-presidential-bid-in-fiasco-event-attended-by-only-a-few |url-status=live}}</ref> In March 2023, a poll showed that 17 percent of Argentines would vote for him and that his political coalition would become the third parliamentary force in the Argentine Congress. His rhetoric was attractive to under-30 voters born during the [[1998–2002 Argentine great depression]] and facing the still ongoing [[economic stagnation]]. His supporters include those who once voted for Kirchnerism but would now vote for Milei as a protest even if they did not support his economic ideas.<ref name="Molina 2023"/>

As inflation rose above 100 percent in May 2023,<ref name="Santamaria 2023">{{cite web |last=Santamaria |first=Carlos |date=15 May 2023 |title=Will Argentina adopt the US dollar? |url=https://www.gzeromedia.com/will-argentina-adopt-the-us-dollar |access-date=20 August 2023 |publisher=GZERO Media |archive-date=18 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230518023359/https://www.gzeromedia.com/will-argentina-adopt-the-us-dollar |url-status=live}}</ref> Milei's position in the polls rose.<ref>{{cite news |date=4 May 2023 |title=Javier Milei, an Argentine libertarian, is rising in the polls |newspaper=The Economist |url=https://www.economist.com/the-americas/2023/05/04/javier-milei-an-argentine-libertarian-is-rising-in-the-polls |access-date=17 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230816140736/https://www.economist.com/the-americas/2023/05/04/javier-milei-an-argentine-libertarian-is-rising-in-the-polls |archive-date=16 August 2023 |issn=0013-0613}}</ref> In June 2023, the markets welcomed [[Sergio Massa]]'s presidential candidacy, as it polarized the election between the ruling party and [[Juntos por el Cambio]], reducing the "Milei factor".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Olveira |first=Dolores |date=30 June 2023 |title=El factor Milei impacta en los mercados: ¿se cae la elección de tercios y aumenta el optimismo? |url=https://www.iprofesional.com/economia/384136-milei-y-mercados-se-cae-la-eleccion-de-tercios-y-hay-optimismo |access-date=25 August 2023 |website=iProfesional |language=es |archive-date=25 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230825203825/https://www.iprofesional.com/economia/384136-milei-y-mercados-se-cae-la-eleccion-de-tercios-y-hay-optimismo |url-status=live}}</ref> Notable moments in Milei's campaign included a viral video of him tearing cards from a wallboard with the names of ministries that he wants to abolish and tossing them into the air as he said ''afuera'' ("out"),<ref>{{cite news |last1=Nugent |first1=Ciara |last2=Stott |first2=Michael |date=2023-08-18 |title=Javier Milei, Argentina's presidential hopeful biting at the establishment's heels |work=Financial Times |url=https://www.ft.com/content/4774b4f9-afb4-46c8-9878-1c8dde70ee74 |access-date=2023-08-20 |archive-date=20 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230820010858/https://www.ft.com/content/4774b4f9-afb4-46c8-9878-1c8dde70ee74 |url-status=live}}</ref> wielding a [[chainsaw]] on stage,<ref name="Centenera 2023">{{cite web |last=Centenera |first=Mar |date=19 November 2023 |title=Javier Milei, a mixture of a messianic preacher and a rock star |url=https://english.elpais.com/international/2023-11-19/javier-milei-a-mixture-of-a-messianic-preacher-and-a-rock-star.html |access-date=28 November 2023 |website=El País English |archive-date=27 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231127234743/https://english.elpais.com/international/2023-11-19/javier-milei-a-mixture-of-a-messianic-preacher-and-a-rock-star.html |url-status=live}}</ref> smashing a piñata on air to symbolize his plans, calling [[Pope Francis]] "a filthy leftist", and praising American gangster [[Al Capone]] as "a hero".<ref name="De Guzman 2023">{{cite magazine |last=De Guzman |first=Chad |date=20 November 2023 |url=https://time.com/6337474/javier-milei-argentina-president-cloned-dogs-advice/ |title=Argentina Just Elected an Eccentric Populist Who Seeks Counsel From His Cloned Dogs |magazine=Time |issn=0040-781X |access-date=28 November 2023 |archive-date=27 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231127235008/https://time.com/6337474/javier-milei-argentina-president-cloned-dogs-advice/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

===Primary and general elections===
{{further|2023 Argentine general election|2023 Argentine primary elections}}
In the August 2023 primary elections, which are seen as an indication of how citizens are likely to vote in the October 2023 general election,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Politi |first1=Daniel |last2=Salomon |first2=Gisela |date=18 August 2023 |title=Argentina's anti-establishment candidate Milei engages IMF in economic talks after shock primary win |url=https://www.sandiegouniontribune.com/news/nation-world/story/2023-08-18/argentinas-anti-establishment-candidate-milei-engages-imf-in-economic-talks-after-shock-primary-win |access-date=28 August 2023 |website=San Diego Union-Tribune |archive-date=28 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230828032836/https://www.sandiegouniontribune.com/news/nation-world/story/2023-08-18/argentinas-anti-establishment-candidate-milei-engages-imf-in-economic-talks-after-shock-primary-win |url-status=live}}</ref> Milei emerged as the leading candidate,<ref name="Reuters 2023">{{cite news |last1=Misculin |first1=Nicolás |last2=Raszewski |first2=Eliana |last3=Grimberg |first3=Candelaria |date=14 August 2023 |title=Argentine far-right outsider Javier Milei posts shock win in primary election |work=Reuters |url=https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/argentina-set-primary-vote-with-ruling-peronists-fighting-survival-2023-08-13 |access-date=14 August 2023 |archive-date=14 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230814022214/https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/argentina-set-primary-vote-with-ruling-peronists-fighting-survival-2023-08-13/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Al Jazeera 2023">{{cite news |date=14 August 2023 |title=Who is Javier Milei, Argentina's far-right populist politician? |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2023/8/14/who-is-javier-milei-argentinas-far-right-populist-politician |access-date=14 August 2023 |work=Al Jazeera |archive-date=14 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230814102604/http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2023/8/14/who-is-javier-milei-argentinas-far-right-populist-politician |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Goñi 2023">{{cite news |last=Goñi |first=Uki |date=2023-08-14 |title=Far-right outsider takes shock lead in Argentina primary election |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/14/argentina-far-right-populist-javier-milei-shock-lead-primary-presidential-elections |access-date=2023-08-14 |issn=0261-3077 |archive-date=14 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230814082008/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/14/argentina-far-right-populist-javier-milei-shock-lead-primary-presidential-elections |url-status=live}}</ref> with 30 percent of the vote, ahead of the traditional Peronism–Kirchnerism and [[Macrism]] that dominated the country in the 2010s.<ref name="Viriglio 2023"/> Milei's victory was celebrated by right-wing figures, including [[Jair Bolsonaro]],<ref name="Goñi 2023" /> [[José Antonio Kast]],<ref name="Goñi 2023" /> [[Ted Cruz]],<ref name="Infobae 2023" /> and the Spanish conservative<ref name="The European Conservative">{{cite news |date=14 July 2024 |title=VOX Breaks Regional Coalitions with Partido Popular |newspaper=The European Conservative |url=https://europeanconservative.com/articles/news/vox-breaks-regional-coalitions-with-partido-popular/ |access-date=13 October 2024}}</ref> political party [[Vox (political party)|Vox]].<ref name="SWI swissinfo.ch 2023">{{cite web |date=14 August 2023 |title=La ultraderecha española felicita a Milei por su victoria en las primarias de Argentina |url=https://www.swissinfo.ch/spa/argentina-elecciones_la-ultraderecha-espa%C3%B1ola-felicita-a-milei-por-su-victoria-en-las-primarias-de-argentina/48733116 |access-date=27 August 2023 |website=SWI swissinfo.ch |language=es |archive-date=27 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230827003710/https://www.swissinfo.ch/spa/argentina-elecciones_la-ultraderecha-espa%C3%B1ola-felicita-a-milei-por-su-victoria-en-las-primarias-de-argentina/48733116 |url-status=live}}</ref> Polls had predicted that Massa would secure the most votes as a candidate in the primaries, with Juntos por el Cambio expected to be the most supported coalition overall;<ref name="The Economist 2023">{{cite news |date=14 August 2023 |title=Argentina could get its first libertarian president |newspaper=The Economist |url=https://www.economist.com/the-americas/2023/08/14/argentina-could-get-its-first-libertarian-president |access-date=14 August 2023 |issn=0013-0613 |archive-date=14 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230814153417/https://www.economist.com/the-americas/2023/08/14/argentina-could-get-its-first-libertarian-president |url-status=live}}</ref> Milei polled at about 20 percent<ref name="Viriglio 2023"/> and was seen as an outsider candidate.<ref>{{cite news |last=Misculin |first=Nicolás |date=17 May 2022 |title=An Argentine libertarian channels inner Trump to 'blow up' political status quo |work=Reuters |url=https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/an-argentine-libertarian-channels-inner-trump-blow-up-political-status-quo-2022-05-17 |access-date=20 August 2023 |archive-date=20 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231120002241/https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/an-argentine-libertarian-channels-inner-trump-blow-up-political-status-quo-2022-05-17/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Sigal |first1=Lucila |last2=Raszewski |first2=Eliana |date=10 August 2023 |title=Argentine conservative leadership battle could be a proxy for presidency race |work=Reuters |url=https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/argentine-conservative-leadership-battle-could-be-proxy-presidency-race-2023-08-10 |access-date=20 August 2023 |archive-date=20 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231120002233/https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/argentine-conservative-leadership-battle-could-be-proxy-presidency-race-2023-08-10/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Initially, for the first round of the general election, with the possibility of a runoff in November,<ref>{{cite web |date=14 August 2023 |title=El peronismo sufre la peor derrota de su historia y la ultraderecha libertaria de Milei gana las primarias argentinas |url=https://www.elmundo.es/internacional/2023/08/14/64d984e3e4d4d8ff6a8b4597.html |access-date=23 August 2023 |website=El Mundo |language=es |archive-date=26 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230826062107/https://www.elmundo.es/internacional/2023/08/14/64d984e3e4d4d8ff6a8b4597.html |url-status=live}}</ref> Peronists saw Milei as a possible ally who would divide the votes of the ''Juntos por el Cambio'' coalition.<ref>{{cite web |date=6 May 2023 |title=La ruleta rusa peronista con Milei |url=https://www.perfil.com/noticias/columnistas/la-ruleta-rusa-peronista-con-milei-por-javier-calvo.phtml |access-date=23 August 2023 |website=Perfil |language=es |archive-date=16 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230816215710/https://www.perfil.com/noticias/columnistas/la-ruleta-rusa-peronista-con-milei-por-javier-calvo.phtml |url-status=live}}</ref>

As a result of his strong performance in the primaries, Milei was considered the front-runner in the general election. His rise has been placed within the context of the last two presidencies of [[Mauricio Macri]] and Alberto Fernández. On 22 October, Milei advanced to the runoff, facing Massa<ref>{{cite news |last1=Watson |first1=Katy |last2=Cursino |first2=Malu |date=23 October 2023 |title=Argentina presidential election: Javier Milei and Sergio Massa head for run-off vote |work=BBC News |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-67190494 |access-date=23 October 2023 |archive-date=23 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231023021115/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-67190494 |url-status=live}}</ref> in what polls showed as a tight race.<ref>{{cite news |last=Feldman |first=Ella |date=20 November 2023 |title=Argentina elects Javier Milei, far-right libertarian with little political experience, as president |work=Courthouse News Service |url=https://www.courthousenews.com/argentina-elects-javier-milei-far-right-libertarian-with-little-political-experience-as-president/ |access-date=3 December 2023 |archive-date=3 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231203015257/https://www.courthousenews.com/argentina-elects-javier-milei-far-right-libertarian-with-little-political-experience-as-president/ |url-status=live}}</ref> In the runoff on 19 November, Milei defeated Massa in a landslide<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/argentina-readies-vote-likely-presidential-election-thriller-2023-11-19/ |title=Argentina awaits election results, media say Milei is ahead &#124; Reuters |work=Reuters |access-date=19 November 2023 |archive-date=19 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231119230955/https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/argentina-readies-vote-likely-presidential-election-thriller-2023-11-19/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Phillips |first1=Tom |last2=Salomón |first2=Josefina |last3=Iglesia |first3=Facundo |date=19 November 2023 |title=Argentina presidential election: far-right libertarian Javier Milei wins after rival concedes |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/20/argentina-presidential-election-far-right-libertarian-javier-milei-wins-after-rival-concedes |access-date=20 November 2023 |issn=0261-3077 |archive-date=19 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231119233050/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/20/argentina-presidential-election-far-right-libertarian-javier-milei-wins-after-rival-concedes |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Chivvis |first1=Christopher |last2=Stuenkel |first2=Oliver |last3=Geaghan‑Breiner |first3=Beatrix |date=22 November 2023 |title=Argentina In the Emerging World Order |url=https://carnegieendowment.org/2023/11/22/argentina-in-emerging-world-order-pub-91088 |access-date=23 November 2023 |publisher=Carnegie Endowment for International Peace |archive-date=27 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240127210856/https://carnegieendowment.org/2023/11/22/argentina-in-emerging-world-order-pub-91088 |url-status=live}}</ref> and a historic election.<ref>{{cite web |date=19 November 2023 |title=Balotaje 2023, en vivo: los resultados y las noticias minuto a minuto de las elecciones |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/politica/balotaje-2023-en-argentina-en-vivo-nid18112023/ |access-date=19 November 2023 |website=La Nación |language=es |archive-date=19 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231119085250/https://www.lanacion.com.ar/politica/balotaje-2023-en-argentina-en-vivo-nid18112023/ |url-status=live}}</ref> It was the highest vote percentage since [[Argentina's transition to democracy]]. Observers generally saw Milei's win as a sign more of discontent with the ''status quo'' than support for his politics,<ref name="De Guzman 2023"/> and his victory was likened to [[Donald Trump]]'s in the United States and [[Jair Bolsonaro]]'s in Brazil.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bayer |first1=Lili |last2=Jones |first2=Sam |last3=Phillips |first3=Tom |last4=Salomón |first4=Josefina |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/20/trump-bolsonaro-javier-milei-argentina-far-right |title=Trump and Bolsonaro salute Javier Milei as far right rejoice around the world |work=The Guardian |date=20 November 2023 |access-date=30 November 2023 |archive-date=30 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231130221420/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/20/trump-bolsonaro-javier-milei-argentina-far-right |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Carmo |first1=Marcia |last2=Corrêa |first2=Alessandra |url=https://www.bbc.com/mundo/articles/c0v29vlel98o |title=Milei presidente: En qué se parece el político argentino a Trump y Bolsonaro |trans-title=President Milei: How the Argentine politician is similar to Trump and Bolsonaro |work=BBC Mundo |language=es |date=21 November 2023 |access-date=30 November 2023 |archive-date=27 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231127071511/https://www.bbc.com/mundo/articles/c0v29vlel98o |url-status=live}}</ref> Within the Argentine Congress, Milei's coalition achieved about 20% in the Chamber of Deputies and 10% in the Senate.<ref>{{cite web |last=Pieper |first=Oliver |date=20 November 2023 |title=Argentina: What to expect from populist President Milei <!--– DW – 11/20/2023--> |url=https://www.dw.com/en/argentina-what-to-expect-from-populist-president-milei/a-67502080 |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=Deutsche Welle |archive-date=3 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231203015257/https://www.dw.com/en/argentina-what-to-expect-from-populist-president-milei/a-67502080 |url-status=live}}</ref> In his victory speech, Milei pledged a new political era,<ref>{{cite news |date=20 November 2023 |title=Right-wing libertarian Milei pledges new political era after Argentina election win |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/video/world/americas/2023/11/20/right-wing-libertarian-milei-pledges-new-political-era-after-argentina-election-win/ |access-date=3 December 2023 |newspaper=The Irish Times |archive-date=3 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231203015256/https://www.irishtimes.com/video/world/americas/2023/11/20/right-wing-libertarian-milei-pledges-new-political-era-after-argentina-election-win/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Bianchi, Elliot & Misculin 2023">{{cite news |last1=Bianchi |first1=Walter |last2=Elliott |first2=Lucinda |last3=Misculin |first3=Nicolás |date=20 November 2023 |title=Argentine libertarian Milei pledges new political era after election win |work=Reuters |url=https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/argentina-readies-vote-likely-presidential-election-thriller-2023-11-19/ |access-date=20 November 2023 |archive-date=19 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231119230955/https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/argentina-readies-vote-likely-presidential-election-thriller-2023-11-19/ |url-status=live}}</ref> vowing to begin "the reconstruction of Argentina" and end its economic decline.<ref name="Bianchi, Elliot & Misculin 2023"/>

