===Inauguration===
{{main|Inauguration of Javier Milei}}
Milei took office as president on 10 December 2023. In addition to a lack of support in Congress,<ref>{{cite web |last=Stuenkel |first=Oliver |date=16 November 2023 |title=The Odds Are Stacked Against Argentina's Next President |url=https://carnegieendowment.org/2023/11/16/odds-are-stacked-against-argentina-s-next-president-pub-91035 |access-date=28 November 2023 |publisher=Carnegie Endowment for International Peace |archive-date=27 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240127211008/https://carnegieendowment.org/2023/11/16/odds-are-stacked-against-argentina-s-next-president-pub-91035 |url-status=live}}</ref> observers pointed to a 200% inflation rate,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Grimberg |first1=Candelaria |last2=Misculin |first2=Nicolás |date=10 December 2023 |url=https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/argentine-libertarian-milei-take-presidency-with-economic-crisis-focus-2023-12-10/ |url-status=live |title=Argentine President Milei warns economic shock unavoidable in maiden speech |work=Reuters |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231210182936/https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/argentine-libertarian-milei-take-presidency-with-economic-crisis-focus-2023-12-10/ |archive-date=10 December 2023 |access-date=10 December 2023}}</ref> rising poverty, and a polarized population as challenges for his presidency.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kahn |first1=Carrie |last2=Martin |first2=Michel |date=20 November 2023 |title=Radical libertarian populist Javier Milei was elected president of Argentina |url=https://www.npr.org/2023/11/20/1214109123/radical-libertarian-populist-javier-milei-was-elected-president-of-argentina |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=NPR |archive-date=3 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231203015257/https://www.npr.org/2023/11/20/1214109123/radical-libertarian-populist-javier-milei-was-elected-president-of-argentina |url-status=live}}</ref> His foreign minister, [[Diana Mondino]], announced that Argentina would not join the [[BRICS]] bloc of developing economies as planned in 2024.<ref>{{cite news |title=Argentina won't join BRICS as scheduled, says member of Milei's transition team |url=https://apnews.com/article/brics-argentina-milei-mondino-e428ca065e093ccb5ecad5d19bc5963d |access-date=3 December 2023 |work=AP NEWS |date=30 November 2023 |archive-date=1 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231201073721/https://apnews.com/article/brics-argentina-milei-mondino-e428ca065e093ccb5ecad5d19bc5963d |url-status=live}}</ref> In his first speech as president, Milei warned of an [[Shock (economics)|economic shock]], described as [[Shock therapy (economics)|shock therapy]] in monetary terms, to be used to fix Argentina's financial woes.<ref>{{cite news |last=Marcarian |first=Agustin |date=10 December 2023 |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2023/12/10/argentine-president-milei-warns-economic-shock-unavoidable-in-maiden-speech.html |url-status=live |title=Argentine President Milei warns economic shock unavoidable in maiden speech |work=CNBC |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231210190443/https://www.cnbc.com/2023/12/10/argentine-president-milei-warns-economic-shock-unavoidable-in-maiden-speech.html |archive-date=10 December 2023 |access-date=10 December 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Biller |first1=David |last2=Eey |first2=Débora |date=10 December 2023 |url=https://apnews.com/article/argentina-milei-inauguration-president-46b73d6a705e1c4652303022a37dbbb0 |url-status=live |title=In inaugural speech, Argentina's Javier Milei prepares nation for painful shock adjustment |work=AP News |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231210182417/https://apnews.com/article/argentina-milei-inauguration-president-46b73d6a705e1c4652303022a37dbbb0 |archive-date=10 December 2023 |access-date=10 December 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Biller |first1=David |last2=Eey |first2=Débora |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2023/12/10/argentina-milei-inauguration-president/c081e654-9719-11ee-9d5c-d462c9032daa_story.html |title=In inaugural speech, Argentina's Javier Milei prepares nation for painful shock adjustment |newspaper=The Washington Post |date=10 December 2023 |issn=0190-8286 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231210193827/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2023/12/10/argentina-milei-inauguration-president/c081e654-9719-11ee-9d5c-d462c9032daa_story.html |archive-date=10 December 2023 |access-date=10 December 2023}}</ref> Following his inauguration, Milei saw his popularity rise. After the first governmental and economic reforms he and his ministers made, 53% of the Argentine people had a good or excellent opinion of him, according to a poll by Aresco on 15 December.<ref>{{cite web |language=es |url=https://www.infobae.com/politica/2023/12/16/una-encuesta-midio-la-primera-semana-de-javier-milei-y-como-impacto-en-la-sociedad-el-anuncio-del-ajuste |title=Una encuesta midió la primera semana de Javier Milei y cómo impactó en la sociedad el anuncio del ajuste |last=Chaves |first=Facundo |date=16 December 2023 |website=Infobae |access-date=16 December 2023 |archive-date=16 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231216093504/https://www.infobae.com/politica/2023/12/16/una-encuesta-midio-la-primera-semana-de-javier-milei-y-como-impacto-en-la-sociedad-el-anuncio-del-ajuste/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

===First acts===
Milei's cabinet includes ministers from [[La Libertad Avanza]] and [[Juntos por el Cambio]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Carpena |first=Ricardo |date=10 December 2023 |url=https://www.infobae.com/politica/2023/12/10/peleas-y-reacomodamientos-comienza-el-gobierno-que-transformara-para-siempre-al-pro-y-a-juntos-por-el-cambio/ |url-status=live |title=Peleas y reacomodamientos: comienza el gobierno que transformará para siempre al PRO y a Juntos por el Cambio |trans-title=Fights and rearrangements: the government that will forever transform the PRO and Together for Change begins |work=Infobae |language=es |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231211000552/https://www.infobae.com/politica/2023/12/10/peleas-y-reacomodamientos-comienza-el-gobierno-que-transformara-para-siempre-al-pro-y-a-juntos-por-el-cambio/ |archive-date=11 December 2023 |access-date=11 December 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Moreno |first=Matías |date=10 December 2023 |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/politica/juntos-por-el-cambio-en-trance-de-descomposicion-y-con-rol-ambiguo-en-el-inicio-del-ciclo-de-milei-nid10122023/ |url-status=live |title=Juntos por el Cambio, en trance de descomposición y con rol ambiguo en el inicio del ciclo de Milei |trans-title=Together for Change, in a state of decomposition and with an ambiguous role in the beginning of the Milei cycle |work=La Nación |language=es |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231211000553/https://www.lanacion.com.ar/politica/juntos-por-el-cambio-en-trance-de-descomposicion-y-con-rol-ambiguo-en-el-inicio-del-ciclo-de-milei-nid10122023/ |archive-date=11 December 2023 |access-date=11 December 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Moreno |first=Matías |date=10 December 2023 |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/politica/con-matices-juntos-por-el-cambio-mostro-una-actitud-colaborativa-tras-el-duro-diagnostico-de-milei-nid10122023/ |url-status=live |title=Con matices, Juntos por el Cambio mostró una actitud colaborativa tras el duro diagnóstico de Milei |trans-title=With nuances, Together for Change showed a collaborative attitude after Milei's harsh diagnosis |work=La Nación |language=es |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231211000808/https://www.lanacion.com.ar/politica/con-matices-juntos-por-el-cambio-mostro-una-actitud-colaborativa-tras-el-duro-diagnostico-de-milei-nid10122023/ |archive-date=11 December 2023 |access-date=11 December 2023}}</ref> In his first acts as president, Milei signed 13 decrees related to his cabinet members. He also lowered the number of ministries from 18 to 9. He appointed three secretariats with portfolio rank, including his sister, to the position of general secretary of the presidency after modifying the anti-[[nepotism]] law prohibiting the appointment of family members.<ref>{{cite news |date=11 December 2023 |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/economia/posse-el-hombre-clave-para-el-futuro-de-las-empresas-publicas-de-acuerdo-al-diseno-del-nuevo-nid11122023/ |url-status=live |title=Nicolás Posse, el hombre clave para el futuro de las empresas públicas de acuerdo al diseño del nuevo gabinete |trans-title=Nicolás Posse, the key man for the future of public companies according to the design of the new cabinet |work=La Nación |language=es |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231211124323/https://www.lanacion.com.ar/economia/posse-el-hombre-clave-para-el-futuro-de-las-empresas-publicas-de-acuerdo-al-diseno-del-nuevo-nid11122023/ |archive-date=11 December 2023 |access-date=11 December 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/dec/31/karina-javier-milei-argentina-president-power |title='El Jefe': is Karina Milei the power behind Argentina's presidential throne? |website=The Gurdian |date=31 December 2023 |first=Josefina |last=Salomón}}</ref>

Milei signed [[Decree 70/2023]], deregulating the Argentine economy. It is subject to approval by Congress, which called for an extraordinary session to be held in the first months of 2024.{{Update inline|date=December 2024|reason=It well beyond the first months of 2024. What happened?}}<ref>{{Cite news |date=2023-12-22 |title=Argentina's Milei orders major deregulation of economy |language=en-IN |work=The Hindu |url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/argentinas-milei-orders-major-deregulation-of-economy/article67662339.ece |access-date=2023-12-25 |issn=0971-751X |archive-date=25 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231225081015/https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/argentinas-milei-orders-major-deregulation-of-economy/article67662339.ece |url-status=live}}</ref> As part of the measure, an estimated 5,000 public sector employees will be affected.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-12-26 |title=Argentina's new president lays off 5,000 government employees hired in 2023, before he took office |url=https://apnews.com/article/argentina-milei-layoffs-cutbacks-economy-7dc274816cdea2fbed6242a39aa94a54 |access-date=2023-12-28 |website=AP News |language=en |archive-date=27 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231227205959/https://apnews.com/article/argentina-milei-layoffs-cutbacks-economy-7dc274816cdea2fbed6242a39aa94a54 |url-status=live}}</ref> An Argentine court halted the labor reforms that were part of the decree.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2024-01-04 |title=Court deals blow to Argentine leader Milei's plan for labour reform |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-67881300 |access-date=2024-01-06 |work=[[BBC]] |language=en-GB |archive-date=6 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240106073451/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-67881300 |url-status=live}}</ref> The CGT also organized a [[Decree 70/2023#Reactions|general strike]] against the proposed policies involving tens of thousands of Argentine workers on a 12-hour strike, which resulted in the cancellation of hundreds of flights.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/argentina-labor-union-holds-strike-biggest-challenge-yet-milei-2024-01-24/ |title=Argentine unions raise challenge to Milei with major strike, protest |author=Nicolás Misculin |date=January 24, 2024 |publisher=Reuters |access-date=January 25, 2024}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/world/americas/argentinas-president-promised-a-free-market-revolution-and-says-hes-delivering-d9ff0eca?mod=hp_lead_pos7|first1=Ryan|last1=Dubé|first2=Emma|last2=Tucker|title=Argentina's President Promised a Free-Market Revolution, and Says He's Delivering|website=The Wall Street Journal|date=January 28, 2024|access-date=28 January 2024|archive-date=28 January 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240128163027/https://www.wsj.com/world/americas/argentinas-president-promised-a-free-market-revolution-and-says-hes-delivering-d9ff0eca?mod=hp_lead_pos7|url-status=live}}</ref>
[[File:Prime Minister Keir Starmer attends the G20 Summit in Brazil (54149827241).jpg|thumb|Milei with Canadian Prime Minister [[Justin Trudeau]] and British Prime Minister [[Keir Starmer]] at the [[2024 G20 Rio de Janeiro summit|2024 G20 summit]] in Rio de Janeiro]]
In a major foreign policy reversal, the Milei administration shelved plans to join [[BRICS]], in which Argentina was slated to participate starting on January 1, 2024.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2023-12-29 |title=Argentina pulls out of plans to join Brics bloc |language=en-GB |work=[[BBC]] |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-67842992 |access-date=2023-12-30 |archive-date=30 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231230155554/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-67842992 |url-status=live}}</ref>

In March 2024, Argentina announced a charge against Venezuela before the [[International Civil Aviation Organization]] for allegedly violating the [[Convention on International Civil Aviation]]. Venezuelan President [[Nicolás Maduro]] banned Argentine aircraft from its airspace earlier amid traded accusations with Milei.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Lejtman |first=Román |date=2024-03-20 |title=Argentina enfrenta a Venezuela en Naciones Unidas por la decisión ilegal de Maduro contra los vuelos de Aerolíneas |url=https://www.infobae.com/politica/2024/03/20/argentina-enfrenta-a-venezuela-en-naciones-unidas-por-la-decision-ilegal-de-maduro-contra-los-vuelos-de-aerolineas/ |access-date=2024-03-21 |website=infobae |language=es-ES}}</ref>

In the same month, Milei approved the transfer of two military [[Mil Mi-17|Mi-171E]] helicopters to Ukraine, which it later received.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Domingo |first1=Juster |title=Argentina Sends Russian-Made Helicopters to Ukraine |url=https://www.thedefensepost.com/2024/03/05/argentina-russia-helicopter-ukraine/?expand_article=1 |access-date=27 March 2024 |work=The Defense Post |date=5 March 2024}}</ref>

On 18 April 2024, the Milei administration formally submitted its request to NATO to become a [[NATO global partners|global partner]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Argentina asks to join NATO as President Milei seeks a more prominent role for his nation |url=https://apnews.com/article/president-milei-argentina-nato-f16s-military-bf56ef4b18646438500c921250c66e93 |access-date=20 April 2024 |work=AP NEWS |date=19 April 2024}}</ref>

Since 24 April 2024, there have been protests by students over the cutting of funds to universities by the Milei administration.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2024-04-24 |title=Buenos Aires: Thousands protest against education cuts |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-68886411 |access-date=2024-04-25 |language=en-GB}}</ref> In May 2024, various unions went on strike against his government for his cuts in spending.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2024-05-10 |title=Argentines strike against spending cuts under Javier Milei |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-68987998 |access-date=2024-05-10 |language=en-GB}}</ref>

[[File:VdL Mercosur 2024.jpg|thumb|Milei and other Mercosur leaders with [[European Commission|EC]] President [[Ursula von der Leyen]] at the 65th Mercosur Summit in Montevideo, Uruguay, 5 December 2024]] 	
In June 2024, during a meeting in Berlin, Milei and German Chancellor [[Olaf Scholz]] expressed support for a [[EU–Mercosur Association Agreement|free trade agreement]] between the EU and [[Mercosur]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Scholz, Milei Demand Swift Deal on EU-Mercosur Free Trade Pact |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-06-23/scholz-milei-demand-swift-deal-on-eu-mercosur-free-trade-pact |work=Bloomberg |date=23 June 2023}}</ref> On 6 December 2024, an agreement on the free trade deal was announced.<ref>{{cite news |title=EU and Mercosur trade bloc finalise free trade deal opposed by France |url=https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20241206-%F0%9F%94%B4-european-union-and-mercosur-trade-bloc-finalise-contentious-free-trade-agreement |access-date=7 December 2024 |work=France 24 |date=6 December 2024 |language=en}}</ref>

According to a popularity poll published by [[Clarín (Argentine newspaper)|Clarín]] on 7 June 2024, most Argentines still had a positive image of their president and an optimistic view of future economic measures taken by the executive branch, despite opposition protests and strikes. In late May, 52.5% of the Argentine people had a positive view of Milei, while 42.2% did not.<ref>{{cite news |language=es |url=https://www.clarin.com/politica/nueva-encuesta-midio-legislativas-2025-dejo-numero-sonado-javier-milei-476_0_Ql0Yz1vl0l.html |title=Una nueva encuesta midió para las legislativas 2025 y dejó un número soñado para Javier Milei: 47,6% |last=Paladini |first=Eduardo |date=7 June 2024 |website=[[Clarín (Argentine newspaper)|Clarín]] |access-date=13 June 2024}}</ref>

===Economy===
Argentina's annual inflation has fallen from 211% in December 2023<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.france24.com/es/am%C3%A9rica-latina/20240111-la-inflaci%C3%B3n-interanual-de-argentina-lleg%C3%B3-al-211-4-en-diciembre-superando-a-la-de-venezuela | title=La inflación interanual de Argentina llegó al 211,4% en diciembre, superando a la de Venezuela | date=11 January 2024 }}</ref> to 193% in October 2024.<ref>https://www.reuters.com/markets/argentinas-inflation-rate-cools-consumers-still-feel-squeezed-2024-11-12/</ref> Monthly inflation slowed in February 2024 for a second consecutive month as Milei continued to push austerity and deregulation measures to revive the country's struggling economy. Argentina's monthly inflation slowed to 13.2% in February, compared to 20.6% in January and 25.5% in December.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-03-12 |title=Argentina inflation slows for a second month as President Milei keeps pushing austerity measures |url=https://apnews.com/article/argentina-inflation-milei-economy-b742f06a3565fbcea24ff925420adf38 |access-date=2024-03-24 |website=AP News |language=en}}</ref> It reached a 3-year low of 2.7% in October 2024, with projections of further decreases.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://apnews.com/article/argentina-inflation-milei-economy-21560cec4fd473a95155adf06ca46c4a | title=Argentina's monthly inflation drops to 2.7%, the lowest level in 3 years | website=[[Associated Press News]] | date=12 November 2024}}</ref> Starting in 2011, the country consistently ran a budget deficit, averaging 4.03% of GDP. Milei achieved a budget surplus within the first few months in office by gutting chunks of the government structure and downsizing it drastically.<ref>https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/argentina-posts-six-months-fiscal-financial-surpluses-2024-07-16/</ref> This led to 20% of federal employees being laid off, saving the government nearly 20 billion dollars in expenses.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://english.elpais.com/international/2024-04-02/president-javier-milei-fires-24000-government-workers-in-argentina-no-one-knows-who-will-be-next.html | title=President Javier Milei fires 24,000 government workers in Argentina: 'No one knows who will be next' | date=2 April 2024}}</ref>

This decrease in the rate of inflation was driven primarily by the Government's elimination of deficit spending, leading to a decrease in monetary expansion.  Decreases in the prices of some key figures in the consumer price index such as electricity and rent have contributed as well.  Rent, for example, has "dropped by 40 percent in real terms, and the supply of rental properties in Buenos Aires has increased by over 300 percent..." as a result of Milei abolishing all forms of [[rent control]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |last=Brattström |first=Rutger |date=2024-10-24 |title=Javier Milei's economic reforms are already paying off in Argentina |url=https://reason.com/2024/10/24/javier-mileis-economic-reforms-are-already-paying-off-in-argentina/?utm_medium=reason_email&utm_source=new_at_reason&utm_campaign=reason_brand&utm_content=Show%20Us%20Your%20Votes,%20Cowards!&utm_term=&time=October%2024th,%202024&mpid=38717&mpweb=2534-4800-38717 |access-date=2024-11-15 |website=Reason.com |language=en-US}}</ref>

In October 2024, Milei announced the shutting down of 'Administración Federal de Ingresos Públicos' (AFIP), the Argentine tax agency. According to Bloomberg Línea, 80 percent of AFIP's 2024 budget was allocated for salary payments. With the restructuring, a significant reduction in staff is anticipated, including the termination of over 3,000 AFIP agents who were "irregularly hired" by the previous administration. The changes will also slash "higher-level positions by 45 percent and lower-level positions by 30 percent," reducing senior officials' salaries. Overall, the measures are expected to "result in budgetary savings of around [6.4 million dollars] per year," the statement added. ''[[Reason (magazine)|Reason]]'' magazine says, "It will be replaced by a newly formed agency, the Agencia de Recaudación y Control Aduanero (ARCA), which will assume some of its functions."<ref>{{cite web | url=https://reason.com/2024/10/22/milei-shuts-down-argentinas-tax-agency/ | title=Milei shuts down Argentina's tax agency | date=22 October 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.bloomberglinea.com/latinoamerica/argentina/milei-confirma-el-cierre-de-la-afip-habra-una-nueva-entidad-tras-fuerte-ajuste/ | title=Milei confirma el cierre de la AFIP: Habrá una nueva entidad tras fuerte ajuste | date=21 October 2024}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Hall |first=Katarina |date=2024-10-22 |title=Milei shuts down Argentina's tax agency |url=https://reason.com/2024/10/22/milei-shuts-down-argentinas-tax-agency/?utm_medium=reason_email&utm_source=new_at_reason&utm_campaign=reason_brand&utm_content=The%20Religious%20Vote%20Is%20Waning%E2%80%94And%20That%20Could%20Spell%20Trouble%20for%20Trump&utm_term=&time=October%2022nd,%202024&mpid=38717&mpweb=2534-4778-38717 |access-date=2024-11-15 |website=Reason.com |language=en-US}}</ref> Meanwhile, Argentina's dollar-denominated international bonds reached new highs in March, with the 2029 and 2030 issues close to or at record-high prices. The bonds have rallied from lows that took the 2030 issue to 18.125 cents in July 2022, fueled by investor bets that the cabinet of Milei will be able to transform the Argentine economy successfully.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Argentina dollar bonds hit record highs as Milei rally powers on |url=https://www.reuters.com/markets/rates-bonds/argentina-dollar-bonds-hit-record-highs-milei-rally-powers-2024-03-22/ |website=Reuters}}</ref>

According to a February 2024 study by the [[Pontifical Catholic University of Argentina]], the poverty rate in January 2024 climbed to 57%, partly attributed to Milei's relaxing of controls on the exchange rate of Argentina's currency as it decreased the reported purchasing power of Argentinians.<ref>{{cite news |last= Calatrava|first=Almudena|date=February 19, 2024 |title=Argentina's poverty levels hit 57% of population, a 20-year high in January, study finds|url=https://apnews.com/article/argentina-poverty-levels-uca-study-milei-devaluation-d5cb0a20b1e768efdeafbad5bf05eded|work=[[The Associated Press]] |location= |access-date=April 3, 2024}}</ref> The move aligned the official and parallel exchange rates more closely. The official exchange rate is a government-set rate used in formal transactions and statistical calculations, such as trade and economic indicators. In contrast, the parallel exchange rate reflects market-driven values influenced by supply and demand and may differ due to factors like government controls or economic conditions. In March 2023, the parallel exchange rate of the peso was worth almost less than half of the official rate.<ref>https://blogs.worldbank.org/en/voices/parallel-exchange-rate-problem-world-banks-approach-helping-people-developing-countries</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://viewpoint.pwc.com/dt/us/en/pwc/in_depths/2023/id202313/202313/id202313.html | title=Argentina: Exchange rate and related disclosure considerations }}</ref><ref>{{cite book | url=https://www.elibrary.imf.org/display/book/9781557753649/ch011.xml | isbn=978-1-55775-364-9 | title=Approaches to Exchange Rate Policy | chapter=Multiple Exchange Rate Systems: The Case of Argentina 9 | date=June 1994 | publisher=International Monetary Fund }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.realinstitutoelcano.org/en/analyses/unravelling-argentinas-economic-maze-raising-prices-to-stop-inflation/ | title=Unravelling Argentina's economic maze: Raising prices to stop inflation}}</ref> 

In July 2024, Milei set up the [[Ministry of Deregulation and State Transformation]] to assist the government in matters related to deregulation, reform, and modernization of the Argentine state.<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2024-07-05 |title=BOLETIN OFICIAL REPUBLICA ARGENTINA – PODER EJECUTIVO – Decreto 585/2024 |url=https://www.boletinoficial.gob.ar/detalleAviso/primera/310123 |website=www.boletinoficial.gob.ar}}<!-- auto-translated from Spanish by Module:CS1 translator --></ref> It is headed by [[Federico Sturzenegger]].<ref>Ignacio Olivera Doll: [https://www.batimes.com.ar/news/amp/economy/federico-sturzenegger-architect-of-argentinas-reforms-says-he-isnt-even-halfway-done.phtml ''Federico Sturzenegger, architect of Argentina’s reforms, says he isn’t even halfway done.''] Buenos Aires Times, 2023-12-23. Retrieved 2024-01-06.</ref>

There has been some criticisms of Milei's approach towards fixing hyperinflation and the economy were its consequences to the poverty rates. During the first six months of his presidency, poverty increased 41.7% to 52.9%. However, poverty was already rising under the previous administration, and hyperinflation accelerated both before and after his inauguration, making it unclear to what extent the increase in poverty is directly linked to his policies.<ref name= "BBC Poverty">{{cite web|access-date=2024-12-10 |title=Argentina records sharp rise in poverty |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/ceqn751x19no |website=www.bbc.com}}</ref> Data for the 3rd Quarter however, broke with historical trends, decreasing to 38.9% with estimates being revised downward for the coming months.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.argentina.gob.ar/noticias/en-el-tercer-trimestre-la-pobreza-se-ubico-en-389-segun-una-proyeccion-oficial | title=En el tercer trimestre la pobreza se ubicó en 38,9% según una proyección oficial }}</ref>

==Political positions==
{{main|Political positions of Javier Milei}}
{{libertarianism sidebar|politicians}}
[[File:Zelensky en la Casa Rosada 3.jpg|thumb|Milei and Ukrainian President [[Volodymyr Zelenskyy]] in Buenos Aires, 10 December 2023]]
[[File:Javier Milei visit to Israel, February 2024 (GPOHZ1 4564).jpg|thumb|right|Milei and Israeli President [[Isaac Herzog]] shake hands in [[Beit HaNassi]] in Jerusalem on 6 February 2024.]]

Milei's stances have been described in many different ways.<ref>{{cite web |date=20 November 2023 |title=Argentinian President Javier Milei's Stance: Anti-Abortion, Anti-Socialism and More |url=https://www.thestatesman.com/world/argentinian-president-javier-mileis-stance-anti-abortion-anti-socialism-and-more-1503242413.html |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=The Statesman |archive-date=3 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231203015256/https://www.thestatesman.com/world/argentinian-president-javier-mileis-stance-anti-abortion-anti-socialism-and-more-1503242413.html |url-status=live}}</ref> He has been variously described as [[Right-libertarianism|right-wing libertarian]],<ref>{{cite news |date=20 November 2023 |title=Analyst View Argentine far-right libertarian Milei sweeps to victory |work=Reuters |url=https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/analyst-view-argentine-far-right-libertarian-milei-sweeps-victory-2023-11-20/ |access-date=3 December 2023 |archive-date=3 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231203150947/https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/analyst-view-argentine-far-right-libertarian-milei-sweeps-victory-2023-11-20/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=20 November 2023 |title=Argentina election: What's next after Javier Milei's victory? |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2023/11/20/argentina-election-whats-next-after-javier-mileis-victory |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=Al Jazeera |archive-date=4 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231204164535/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2023/11/20/argentina-election-whats-next-after-javier-mileis-victory |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Meredith |first=Sam |date=21 November 2023 |title=China says it stands ready to work with Argentina despite Milei criticism |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2023/11/21/milei-china-says-it-would-be-a-huge-mistake-for-argentina-to-cut-ties.html |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=CNBC |archive-date=3 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231203015257/https://www.cnbc.com/2023/11/21/milei-china-says-it-would-be-a-huge-mistake-for-argentina-to-cut-ties.html |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Ultraconservatism|ultraconservative]],<ref>{{cite news |last=Feldman |first=Ella |date=16 October 2023 |title=As inflation skyrockets, Argentina must choose: Far-right outsider or status quo for president? |work=Courthouse News Service |url=https://www.courthousenews.com/as-inflation-skyrockets-argentina-must-choose-outsider-or-status-quo-for-president/ |access-date=3 December 2023 |archive-date=19 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231119064705/https://www.courthousenews.com/as-inflation-skyrockets-argentina-must-choose-outsider-or-status-quo-for-president/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Criales |first=José Pablo |date=13 November 2023 |title=Sergio Massa drags Javier Milei through the mud in Argentina's last presidential debate: 'Is Margaret Thatcher your role model?' |url=https://english.elpais.com/international/2023-11-13/sergio-massa-drags-javier-milei-through-the-mud-in-argentinas-latest-presidential-debate-is-margaret-thatcher-your-role-model.html |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=El País English |archive-date=3 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231203015256/https://english.elpais.com/international/2023-11-13/sergio-massa-drags-javier-milei-through-the-mud-in-argentinas-latest-presidential-debate-is-margaret-thatcher-your-role-model.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Bulbul |first=Nuray |date=20 November 2023 |title=Who is Javier Milei, Argentina's new hard-right president? |url=https://ca.finance.yahoo.com/news/javier-milei-argentinas-hard-president-142340903.html |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=Yahoo Finance |archive-date=3 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231203015256/https://ca.finance.yahoo.com/news/javier-milei-argentinas-hard-president-142340903.html |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Far-right politics|far-right]],<ref>{{cite news |last=Buschschlüter |first=Vanessa |date=19 November 2023 |title=Javier Milei: Argentina's far-right outsider wins presidential election |work=BBC News |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-67470549 |access-date=3 December 2023 |archive-date=24 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231124015721/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-67470549 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Phillips |first=Tom |date=20 November 2023 |title=Who is Javier Milei? Argentina's new far-right president 'El Loco' takes the stage |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/20/who-is-javier-milei-argentina-new-president-far-right-what-does-he-stand-for |access-date=3 December 2023 |issn=0261-3077 |archive-date=2 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231202214557/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/20/who-is-javier-milei-argentina-new-president-far-right-what-does-he-stand-for |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Oner |first=Imdat |date=22 November 2023 |title=Javier Milei's Victory: A New Chapter for Right-Wing Populism in Argentina?<!-- - ECPS--> |url=https://www.populismstudies.org/javier-mileis-victory-a-new-chapter-for-right-wing-populism-in-argentina/ |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=Populism Studies |archive-date=3 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231203015257/https://www.populismstudies.org/javier-mileis-victory-a-new-chapter-for-right-wing-populism-in-argentina/ |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Right-wing populism|right-wing populist]],<ref>{{cite web |last=Kahn |first=Carrie |date=19 November 2023 |title=Javier Milei, a radical libertarian populist, elected president of Argentina |url=https://www.npr.org/2023/11/19/1214092698/javier-milei-a-radical-libertarian-populist-elected-president-of-argentina |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=NPR |archive-date=28 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231128233703/https://www.npr.org/2023/11/19/1214092698/javier-milei-a-radical-libertarian-populist-elected-president-of-argentina |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=20 November 2023 |title=Argentina elects far-right populist Javier Milei 'the madman' as new president |work=ITV News |url=https://www.itv.com/news/2023-11-20/argentina-elects-far-right-populist-javier-milei-as-new-president |access-date=3 December 2023 |archive-date=3 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231203015257/https://www.itv.com/news/2023-11-20/argentina-elects-far-right-populist-javier-milei-as-new-president |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=20 November 2023 |title=Far-right populist Javier Milei becomes Argentina's new president |url=https://www.euronews.com/2023/11/20/far-right-populist-javier-milei-becomes-argentinas-new-president |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=Euronews |archive-date=30 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231130234949/https://www.euronews.com/2023/11/20/far-right-populist-javier-milei-becomes-argentinas-new-president |url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Market fundamentalism|ultra-liberal]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Genoux |first=Flora |date=8 November 2023 |title=Argentina: Far-right candidate Javier Milei leaves the business community skeptical |work=Le Monde |url=https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2023/11/08/argentina-ultraliberal-candidate-javier-milei-leaves-the-business-community-skeptical_6235644_4.html |access-date=3 December 2023 |archive-date=3 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231203015256/https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2023/11/08/argentina-ultraliberal-candidate-javier-milei-leaves-the-business-community-skeptical_6235644_4.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Fest |first=Sebastián |date=19 November 2023 |title=Javier Milei, el ultraliberal que promete poner patas arriba a Argentina y llevar a mínimos el vínculo con España |url=https://www.elmundo.es/internacional/2023/11/20/655a9a8cfdddffc8b48b4578.html |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=El Mundo |language=es |archive-date=3 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231203015256/https://www.elmundo.es/internacional/2023/11/20/655a9a8cfdddffc8b48b4578.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Chitre |first=Manjiri |date=20 November 2023 |title=Who is Javier Milei, Argentina's new 'shock therapy' libertarian President? |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/world-news/who-is-javier-milei-argentinas-new-shock-therapy-libertarian-president-101700441962055.html |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=Hindustan Times |archive-date=1 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231201051731/https://www.hindustantimes.com/world-news/who-is-javier-milei-argentinas-new-shock-therapy-libertarian-president-101700441962055.html |url-status=live}}</ref> In reality, he is a philosophical [[anarcho-capitalist]] who is, for practical purposes, a [[Night-watchman state|minarchist]], Milei advocates [[Night-watchman state|minimal government]], focusing on justice and security,<ref name="Il Post 2023"/> with a philosophy rooted in [[Life, Liberty and the pursuit of Happiness#Lockean roots hypothesis|life, liberty, and property]], and [[free market]] principles. He criticizes [[socialism]] and [[communism]],<ref name="Cronista 2019">{{cite web |date=12 February 2019 |title=La charla TEDx de Milei donde explica la 'belleza' del capitalismo |url=https://www.cronista.com/infotechnology/online/La-charla-TEDx-de-Milei-donde-explica-la-belleza-del-capitalismo-20190212-0002.html |access-date=19 August 2023 |website=Cronista |language=es |archive-date=19 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230819174443/https://www.cronista.com/infotechnology/online/La-charla-TEDx-de-Milei-donde-explica-la-belleza-del-capitalismo-20190212-0002.html |url-status=live}}</ref> advocating [[economic liberalization]] and restructuring government ministries.<ref>{{Cite web |date=4 August 2023 |title=Punto por punto: el plan de gobierno que presentó Javier Milei |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/economia/punto-por-punto-el-plan-de-gobierno-que-presento-javier-milei-nid02082023/ |access-date=5 September 2023 |website=La Nación |language=es |archive-date=30 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231030105011/https://www.lanacion.com.ar/economia/punto-por-punto-el-plan-de-gobierno-que-presento-javier-milei-nid02082023/ |url-status=live}}</ref> He opposes Argentina's Central Bank and current taxation policies.<ref name="Centenera & Criales 2023">{{cite web |last1=Centenera |first1=Mar |last2=Criales |first2=José Pablo |date=14 August 2023 |title=Ultra-conservative Javier Milei capitalizes on the protest vote and wins Argentina's primaries |url=https://english.elpais.com/international/2023-08-14/ultra-conservative-javier-milei-capitalizes-on-the-protest-vote-and-wins-argentinas-primaries.html |access-date=16 August 2023 |website=El País English |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230815234239/https://english.elpais.com/international/2023-08-14/ultra-conservative-javier-milei-capitalizes-on-the-protest-vote-and-wins-argentinas-primaries.html |archive-date=15 August 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Gillespie |first1=Patrick |last2=Tobías |first2=Manuela |date=14 August 2023 |title=Who is Javier Milei, the Central Bank-Hating Economist Who Upended Argentine Polls? |url=https://www.bloomberglinea.com/english/who-is-javier-milei-the-central-bank-hating-economist-who-upended-argentine-polls |access-date=24 August 2023 |website=Bloomberg Línea |archive-date=24 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230824084112/https://www.bloomberglinea.com/english/who-is-javier-milei-the-central-bank-hating-economist-who-upended-argentine-polls/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

Economically, Milei is influenced by the [[Austrian school of economics|Austrian school]] and admires former president [[Carlos Menem]]'s policies.<ref name="Fiore Viani 2021">{{cite web |last=Fiore Viani |first=Gonzalo |date=10 September 2021 |title=Milei y los libertarios: una corriente (no tan) nueva en la política argentina |url=https://agendapublica.elpais.com/noticia/17145/milei-libertarios-corriente-no-tan-nueva-politica-argentina |access-date=20 August 2023 |website=Agenda Pública |language=es |archive-date=19 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230819220045/https://agendapublica.elpais.com/noticia/17145/milei-libertarios-corriente-no-tan-nueva-politica-argentina |url-status=live}}</ref> He supports [[capitalism]], viewing socialism as embodying envy and coercion.<ref name="Cronista 2019" /> Milei proposes reducing government ministries and addressing economic challenges through spending cuts and fiscal reforms, criticizing previous administrations for excessive spending.<ref name="Viriglio 2023" /><ref>{{cite tweet |number=1691737260813688997 |user=electo_mania |title=La propuesta de Javier Milei con los ministerios |author=EM-electomania.es |date=16 August 2023 |access-date=16 August 2023 |language=es}}</ref> He has praised the monetary policies of former British prime minister [[Margaret Thatcher]] and called her "a great leader".<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/13/javier-milei-argentina-thatcher-praise-falklands-veterans |title=Argentina's far-right Milei angers Falklands veterans with Thatcher praise |work=The Guardian |date=13 November 2023 |access-date=20 November 2023 |archive-date=18 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231118174842/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/13/javier-milei-argentina-thatcher-praise-falklands-veterans |url-status=live |last=Goñi |first=Uki}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/margaret-thatcher-a-great-leader-argentine-candidate-declares-02x387520 |title=Margaret Thatcher 'a great leader', Argentine candidate declares |website=[[The Times]] |date=14 November 2023 |access-date=20 November 2023 |archive-date=15 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231115013850/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/margaret-thatcher-a-great-leader-argentine-candidate-declares-02x387520 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/argentinas-javier-milei-radical-who-could-blow-up-political-status-quo-2023-11-16/ |title=Argentina's Javier Milei: the radical who could blow up political status quo |work=Reuters |date=17 November 2023 |access-date=20 November 2023 |archive-date=19 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231119115205/https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/argentinas-javier-milei-radical-who-could-blow-up-political-status-quo-2023-11-16/ |url-status=live |last1=Heath |first1=Maximilian}}</ref>

Milei opposes [[abortion]] and [[euthanasia]],<ref>{{Cite web |last=Brandimarte |first=Walter |date=15 August 2023 |title=Here are candidate Javier Milei's proposals for Argentina |url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/world/2023/08/15/politics/javier-milei-proposals-argentina/ |access-date=3 September 2023 |website=The Japan Times |archive-date=22 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231022112126/https://www.japantimes.co.jp/world/2023/08/15/politics/javier-milei-proposals-argentina/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=25 September 2021 |title=Economia argentina é um vulcão a ponto de estalar, diz Javier Milei, líder dos libertários |url=https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/mundo/2021/09/economia-argentina-e-um-vulcao-a-ponto-de-estalar-diz-javier-milei-lider-dos-libertarios.shtml |access-date=23 August 2023 |website=Folha de S.Paulo |language=pt |archive-date=23 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230823123306/https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/mundo/2021/09/economia-argentina-e-um-vulcao-a-ponto-de-estalar-diz-javier-milei-lider-dos-libertarios.shtml |url-status=live}}</ref> is indifferent to [[same-sex marriage]], and supports [[privatization]] in education and healthcare. He opposes [[Vaccination policy|mandatory vaccination]] and supports [[Drug liberalization|drug legalization]] and the [[Prostitution law#Regulated prostitution|legalization of prostitution]].<ref name="Rossi 2021">{{cite web |last=Rossi |first=Paula |date=22 November 2021 |title='Soy re provacunas': la explicación de Javier Milei de por qué decidió darse las dosis contra el Covid |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/politica/soy-re-provacunas-la-explicacion-de-javier-milei-de-por-que-decidio-darse-las-dosis-contra-el-covid-nid22112021 |access-date=27 August 2023 |website=La Nación |language=es |archive-date=27 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230827232931/https://www.lanacion.com.ar/politica/soy-re-provacunas-la-explicacion-de-javier-milei-de-por-que-decidio-darse-las-dosis-contra-el-covid-nid22112021/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="El Cronista 2023">{{cite web |date=9 August 2021 |title=Cinco definiciones fuertes de Javier Milei: armas, drogas, homosexualidad, aborto y el Estado como enemigo |url=https://www.cronista.com/economia-politica/cinco-definiciones-fuertes-de-javier-milei-aborto-drogas-armas-homosexualidad-y-el-estado-enemigo |access-date=17 August 2023 |website=El Cronista |language=es |archive-date=10 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231010053630/http://www.cronista.com/economia-politica/cinco-definiciones-fuertes-de-javier-milei-aborto-drogas-armas-homosexualidad-y-el-estado-enemigo/ |url-status=live}}</ref> As a supporter of the [[right to keep and bear arms]], Milei advocates for the deregulation of firearm ownership and proposes [[Opposition to immigration|immigration restrictions]] for criminals.<ref name="Il Post 2023" /><ref>{{cite web |title=Javier Milei: 'Estoy a favor de la libre portación de armas' |url=https://www.infobae.com/politica/2022/05/27/javier-milei-estoy-a-favor-de-la-libre-portacion-de-arma |access-date=14 August 2023 |website=Infobae |date=27 May 2022 |language=es |archive-date=20 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230120214105/https://www.infobae.com/politica/2022/05/27/javier-milei-estoy-a-favor-de-la-libre-portacion-de-arma/ |url-status=live}}</ref> In foreign policy, Milei criticizes the [[International Monetary Fund|IMF]],<ref name="Nugent 2023">{{cite news |last=Nugent |first=Ciara |date=6 August 2023 |title=Argentina's far-right libertarian wants tougher austerity to rebuild troubled economy |work=Financial Times |url=https://www.ft.com/content/782197c9-35dd-42e4-96f3-910cf60e9ecf |access-date=20 August 2023 |archive-date=20 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230820000626/https://www.ft.com/content/782197c9-35dd-42e4-96f3-910cf60e9ecf |url-status=live}}</ref> opposes [[trade union]]s,<ref name="Infonews.com 2023">{{cite web |date=9 August 2023 |title=Milei aseguró que el artículo 14 bis de la Constitución es 'el cáncer' del país |url=https://infonews.com/milei-aseguro-que-el-articulo-14-bis-de-la-constitucion-es-el-cancer-del-pais.html |access-date=19 August 2023 |website=Infonews.com |archive-date=19 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230819012920/https://infonews.com/milei-aseguro-que-el-articulo-14-bis-de-la-constitucion-es-el-cancer-del-pais.html |url-status=live}}</ref> aligns with [[Criticism of socialism|anti-socialist]] figures of the [[Americas]] like [[Donald Trump]] and [[Jair Bolsonaro]],<ref>{{cite web |date=15 February 2023 |title=Javier Milei tuvo una videollamada con Jair Bolsonaro y coincidieron en 'unir fuerzas para luchar contra el socialismo' |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/politica/javier-milei-tuvo-una-videollamada-con-jair-bolsonaro-y-coincidieron-en-unir-fuerzas-para-luchar-nid15022023/ |access-date=27 August 2023 |website=La Nación |language=es |archive-date=27 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230827023212/https://www.lanacion.com.ar/politica/javier-milei-tuvo-una-videollamada-con-jair-bolsonaro-y-coincidieron-en-unir-fuerzas-para-luchar-nid15022023/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Gosman 2023">{{cite web |last=Gosman |first=Eleonora |date=18 August 2023 |title=Javier Milei y la internacional de derecha |url=https://www.perfil.com/noticias/opinion/javier-milei-y-la-internacional-de-derecha.phtml |access-date=27 August 2023 |website=Perfil |language=es |archive-date=27 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230827023210/https://www.perfil.com/noticias/opinion/javier-milei-y-la-internacional-de-derecha.phtml |url-status=live}}</ref> and prioritizes alliances with the United States and Israel.<ref>{{cite web |date=14 August 2023 |title=Argentina's Far-right Presidential Candidate Studies Torah, Mulls Conversion to Judaism and Is an Avowed Fan of Israel |url=https://www.haaretz.com/world-news/2023-08-14/ty-article/.premium/an-argentinian-presidential-candidate-studies-torah-and-supports-jerusalem-embassy-move/00000189-f446-d8b0-a1bd-fcd663eb0000 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230816035443/https://www.haaretz.com/world-news/2023-08-14/ty-article/.premium/an-argentinian-presidential-candidate-studies-torah-and-supports-jerusalem-embassy-move/00000189-f446-d8b0-a1bd-fcd663eb0000 |archive-date=16 August 2023 |url-status=live |access-date=15 August 2023 |website=Haaretz}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=15 August 2023 |title=Javier Milei: 'Si soy presidente, mis aliados son EEUU e Israel' |url=https://www.diariolasamericas.com/america-latina/javier-milei-si-soy-presidente-mis-aliados-son-eeuu-e-israel-n5341381 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230816162737/https://www.diariolasamericas.com/america-latina/javier-milei-si-soy-presidente-mis-aliados-son-eeuu-e-israel-n5341381 |archive-date=16 August 2023 |url-status=live |access-date=15 August 2023 |website=Diario Las Américas |language=es}}</ref> He is cautious about relations with China<ref name="Brandimarte & Tobias 2023">{{cite news |last1=Brandimarte |first1=Walter |last2=Tobias |first2=Manuela |date=16 August 2023 |title=Argentina's Milei Says He'd Reject 'Assassin' China, Leave Mercosur |work=Bloomberg News |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-08-16/milei-s-foreign-policy-reject-assassin-china-leave-mercosur |access-date=25 August 2023 |archive-date=8 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231108050728/http://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-08-16/milei-s-foreign-policy-reject-assassin-china-leave-mercosur |url-status=live}}</ref> and supports Ukraine against Russia in the latter's [[Russian invasion of Ukraine|ongoing invasion]].<ref>{{cite web |date=1 March 2022 |title=Insólita sesión: Milei llegó embanderado de Ucrania y otro diputado en monopatín |url=https://www.cronica.com.ar/politica/Insolita-sesion-Milei-llego-embanderado-de-Ucrania-y-otro-diputado-en-monopatin-20220301-0095.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220307202523/https://www.cronica.com.ar/politica/Insolita-sesion-Milei-llego-embanderado-de-Ucrania-y-otro-diputado-en-monopatin-20220301-0095.html |archive-date=7 March 2022 |url-status=live |access-date=16 August 2023 |website=Cronica |language=es}}</ref>

Milei advocates for dialogue with the [[United Kingdom]] over the [[Falkland Islands sovereignty dispute]].<ref name="Alonso 2023"/> In May 2024, he indicated his general acceptance of the [[Falkland Islands]]' status as a [[British Overseas Territories|British Overseas Territory]] for the time being, accepting that it could take decades for Argentina to gain control over them. Though asserting that Argentine would not "relinquish our sovereignty" over the islands, Milei said he would not "seek conflict with the United Kingdom", preferring to resolve the dispute "within the framework of peace."<ref name="decades_2024_05_06_bbc">Wells,Ione; South America correspondent: [https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/ce43zv3qln9o "Falklands dispute may last decades – Argentina president,"] May 6, 2024, [[BBC News]], retrieved May 7, 2024</ref>

==Public image==
{{main|Public image of Javier Milei}}
Milei has cultivated a complex and controversial public image marked by a blend of [[Populism|populist]], right-wing libertarian, and [[Conservatism|conservative]] ideologies. Known for his [[Market fundamentalism|ultra-liberal]] economic views and [[Right-wing populism|right-wing populist]] rhetoric, Milei's political stance has been subject to various interpretations by international media and political commentators.<ref name="Molina 2023"/><ref name="Alonso 2023"/> His rise to prominence during the 2023 presidential campaign, fueled by his primary win, sparked widespread attention,<ref name="Reuters 2023"/><ref name="Al Jazeera 2023"/><ref name="Goñi 2023"/> as did his [[central bank]] abolition and [[Currency substitution|dollarization]] proposals.<ref name="Sivak 2023">{{cite web |last=Sivak |first=Martín |date=25 July 2023 |title=Javier Milei, presidential candidate: 'It's super easy to dollarize Argentina's economy' |url=https://english.elpais.com/international/2023-07-25/javier-milei-presidential-candidate-its-super-easy-to-dollarize-argentinas-economy.html |access-date=15 August 2023 |website=El País English |archive-date=15 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230815005030/https://english.elpais.com/international/2023-07-25/javier-milei-presidential-candidate-its-super-easy-to-dollarize-argentinas-economy.html |url-status=live}}</ref>
[[File:Javier Milei recibe a Viktor Orbán 2.jpg|thumb|upright=0.9|Milei with Hungarian Prime Minister [[Viktor Orbán]]]]
Milei is known for his flamboyant personality, distinctive personal style, and strong media presence, which sometimes causes controversy, and his embrace of [[Conspiracy theory|conspiracy theories]],<ref>{{cite news |last=Nicas |first=Jack |date=19 November 2023 |title=Argentina Elects Javier Milei in Victory for Far Right |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/19/world/americas/argentina-election-javier-milei.html |access-date=9 December 2023 |issn=0362-4331 |archive-date=19 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231119232617/https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/19/world/americas/argentina-election-javier-milei.html |url-status=live}}</ref> including the [[Cultural Marxism conspiracy theory]].<ref>{{cite web |date=1 May 2023 |title=Can a far-right populist win in Argentina? |url=https://www.gzeromedia.com/viewpoint/can-a-far-right-populist-win-in-argentina |access-date=14 August 2023 |publisher=GZERO Media |archive-date=14 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230814213459/https://www.gzeromedia.com/viewpoint/can-a-far-right-populist-win-in-argentina |url-status=live}}</ref> He has also called the idea of [[climate change]] as an anthropogenic phenomenon "a socialist lie" and said that concerns about it are nothing more than "deceptions promoted by the neo-Marxists",<ref>{{cite web |last=Politi |first=Daniel |date=28 August 2023 |title=Right-wing populist Javier Milei gains support in Argentina by blasting 'political caste' |url=https://apnews.com/article/javier-milei-argentina-elections-presidency-54671463bcf1a3ef22e7f7a2a602adcd |access-date=27 August 2023 |website=AP News |archive-date=27 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230827184632/https://apnews.com/article/javier-milei-argentina-elections-presidency-54671463bcf1a3ef22e7f7a2a602adcd |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Gosman 2023"/> as are those related to the [[attempts to overturn the 2020 United States presidential election]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Tharoor |first=Ishaan |date=21 November 2023 |title=<!--Analysis |-->Javier Milei's perilous quest to 'make Argentina great again' |newspaper=The Washington Post |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2023/11/21/milei-trump-bolsonaro-argentina-election/ |access-date=9 December 2023 |issn=0190-8286 |archive-date=22 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231122134504/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2023/11/21/milei-trump-bolsonaro-argentina-election/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Echoing [[Donald Trump]], he also claimed electoral fraud ahead of the 2023 presidential runoff.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Iglesia |first1=Facundo |last2=Phillips |first2=Tom |date=17 November 2023 |title=Milei fraud claims echo Trump ahead of Argentinian presidential runoff |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/17/milei-argentina-election-fraud-trump |access-date=9 December 2023 |issn=0261-3077 |archive-date=11 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231211024127/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/17/milei-argentina-election-fraud-trump |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Biller |first1=David |last2=Politi |first2=Daniel |date=18 November 2023 |title=Milei echoes Trump with fraud claims that inject uncertainty into Argentina's presidential runoff |url=https://apnews.com/article/argentina-milei-massa-fraud-election-runoff-683332bb71bc2084c604e22c5919e144 |access-date=12 December 2023 |website=AP News |archive-date=2 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231202122600/https://apnews.com/article/argentina-milei-massa-fraud-election-runoff-683332bb71bc2084c604e22c5919e144 |url-status=live}}</ref> Like other right-wing populists, his rhetoric focuses on opposing what he calls "the political caste".<ref name="Dadouch 2023"/> Milei's party was criticized for including among his candidates alleged [[Neo-Nazism|neo-Nazis]] and apologists for the [[National Reorganization Process]].<ref name="iProfesional 2023"/> During his political career, Milei has also been involved in several investigations and has been accused of having a violent attitude toward journalists and critics, as well as of misogynistic behavior, including toward women in journalism.<ref name="BBC News Mundo 2023"/>

Milei is a [[cosplay]]er with a [[superhero]] persona called "General AnCap".<ref>{{cite web |date=15 November 2023 |title=Populist Javier Milei is rallying for the Argentine presidency with chainsaws and Comic-Con costumes |url=https://apnews.com/article/argentina-javier-milei-election-ea4b2b181ab98a60a9dc96572c27005b |access-date=20 November 2023 |website=AP News |archive-date=19 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231119052046/https://apnews.com/article/argentina-javier-milei-election-ea4b2b181ab98a60a9dc96572c27005b |url-status=live}}</ref> He also champions [[free love]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/2069706-el-amor-segun-el-economista-javier-milei |url-status=dead |title=El amor, según el economista Javier Milei |work=La Nación |language=es |date=5 October 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171006041159/https://www.lanacion.com.ar/2069706-el-amor-segun-el-economista-javier-milei |archive-date=6 October 2017 |access-date=15 August 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=24 June 2018 |title=Javier Milei, experto en economía, tríos sexuales y sexo tántrico: 'Puedo estar sin eyacular tres meses' |url=https://www.infobae.com/teleshow/paso-en-la-tv/2018/06/24/javier-milei-experto-en-economia-trios-sexuales-y-sexo-tantrico-puedo-estar-sin-eyacular-tres-meses |access-date=15 August 2023 |website=Infobae |language=es |archive-date=16 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230816162051/https://www.infobae.com/teleshow/paso-en-la-tv/2018/06/24/javier-milei-experto-en-economia-trios-sexuales-y-sexo-tantrico-puedo-estar-sin-eyacular-tres-meses/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Gibbs |first=Stephen |date=17 August 2023 |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/argentina-javier-milei-far-right-primary-election-2023-n86rvvrr2 |url-status=live |title=Argentina's Trump, Javier Milei, takes surprise lead in race for power |work=The Times |issn=0140-0460 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230815221523/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/argentina-javier-milei-far-right-primary-election-2023-n86rvvrr2 |archive-date=15 August 2023 |access-date=16 August 2023}}</ref> In addition to being nicknamed ''el Peluca'' ("The Wig") for his eccentric hair,<ref>{{cite web |date=28 July 2016 |title=Javier Milei, el economista del peinado raro |url=https://www.clarin.com/espectaculos/fama/javier_milei-alejandro_fantino-animales_sueltos_0_HkbsG9Du.html |access-date=15 August 2023 |website=Clarín |language=es |archive-date=16 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230816203700/https://www.clarin.com/espectaculos/fama/javier_milei-alejandro_fantino-animales_sueltos_0_HkbsG9Du.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Ash |first=Hugo |date=22 April 2018 |url=http://www.perfil.com/noticias/columnistas/el-ultimo-que-pague-la-luz.phtml |url-status=dead |title=El último que pague la luz |website=Perfil |language=es |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230814105226/https://www.perfil.com/noticias/columnistas/el-ultimo-que-pague-la-luz.phtml |archive-date=14 August 2023 |access-date=14 August 2023}}<!--This nickname is briefly referred to by the article as an off-topic mention.--></ref><ref>{{cite web |date=14 August 2023 |title=Far-right populist Milei finishes first in Argentina's presidential primary |url=https://www.france24.com/en/video/20230814-far-right-populist-milei-finishes-first-in-argentina-s-presidential-primary |access-date=15 August 2023 |website=France 24 |archive-date=15 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230815111830/https://www.france24.com/en/video/20230814-far-right-populist-milei-finishes-first-in-argentina-s-presidential-primary |url-status=live}}</ref> which has been compared to that of Trump and fellow right-wing populists [[Boris Johnson]] and [[Geert Wilders]],<ref>{{cite web |last=Peláez |first=Raquel |date=28 November 2023 |title=Right-wing politics and crazy hair: When a haircut becomes a political manifesto |url=https://english.elpais.com/lifestyle/2023-11-28/right-wing-politics-and-crazy-hair-when-a-haircut-becomes-a-political-manifesto.html |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=El País English |archive-date=3 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231203015257/https://english.elpais.com/lifestyle/2023-11-28/right-wing-politics-and-crazy-hair-when-a-haircut-becomes-a-political-manifesto.html |url-status=live}}</ref> Milei is known as ''el Loco'' ("The Crazy One").<ref name="González 2023">{{cite magazine |last=González |first=Juan Luis |date=9 August 2023 |title=Milei y su perro muerto: quién es la fuente secreta de 'El Loco', el libro sobre él |url=https://noticias.perfil.com/noticias/politica/milei-y-su-perro-muerto-quien-es-la-fuente-secreta-de-el-loco-el-libro-sobre-el.phtml |access-date=25 August 2023 |magazine=Revista Noticias |language=es |archive-date=24 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230824170609/https://noticias.perfil.com/noticias/politica/milei-y-su-perro-muerto-quien-es-la-fuente-secreta-de-el-loco-el-libro-sobre-el.phtml |url-status=live}}</ref> News outlets have called him a "rock singer and tantric sex instructor",<ref name="Crisp 2023">{{cite news |last=Crisp |first=James |date=14 August 2023 |title=Hard-Right rock singer and 'tantric sex instructor' takes shock lead in Argentinian elections |work=The Telegraph |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2023/08/14/javier-milei-argentina-elections-far-right-trump-bolsonaro |access-date=14 August 2023 |issn=0307-1235 |archive-date=14 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230814213456/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2023/08/14/javier-milei-argentina-elections-far-right-trump-bolsonaro/ |url-status=live}}</ref> a "former tantric sex coach",<ref name="Goñi 2023" /> and a "mixture of a messianic preacher and a rock star",<ref name="Centenera 2023"/> and have likened him to both Trump and [[Wolverine (character)|Wolverine]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Phillips |first=Tom |date=20 November 2023 |title=Who is Javier Milei? Argentina's new far-right president 'El Loco' takes the stage |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/20/who-is-javier-milei-argentina-new-president-far-right-what-does-he-stand-for |access-date=28 November 2023 |issn=0261-3077 |archive-date=27 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231127234137/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/20/who-is-javier-milei-argentina-new-president-far-right-what-does-he-stand-for |url-status=live}}</ref> His admirers also call him "The Lion" because of the lyrics of the song "Panic Show" by rock band [[La Renga]], which he sings in his public acts, coupled with his looks (in particular, his long hair).<ref>{{cite web |last1=Abd |first1=Rodrigo |last2=Politi |first2=Daniel |date=15 November 2023 |title=Populist Javier Milei is rallying for the Argentine presidency with chainsaws and Comic-Con costumes |url=https://apnews.com/article/argentina-javier-milei-election-ea4b2b181ab98a60a9dc96572c27005b |access-date=15 December 2023 |website=AP News |archive-date=19 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231119052046/https://apnews.com/article/argentina-javier-milei-election-ea4b2b181ab98a60a9dc96572c27005b |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Armstrong |first=Rory Elliott |date=18 November 2023 |title=Who is Argentina's controversial chainsaw presidential candidate? |url=https://www.euronews.com/2023/11/18/who-is-argentinas-controversial-chainsaw-presidential-candidate-javier-milei |access-date=28 November 2023 |website=Euronews |archive-date=27 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231127200630/https://www.euronews.com/2023/11/18/who-is-argentinas-controversial-chainsaw-presidential-candidate-javier-milei |url-status=live}}</ref> In 2024, ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' named him one of the [[Time 100|100 most influential people in the world]], stating that "with Milei in office, there will be no going back for Argentina."<ref>{{cite web |last=Vera |first=Bergengruen |date=17 April 2024 |title= Javier Milei is on the 2024 TIME100 list |url=https://time.com/6965017/javier-milei/ |access-date=17 April 2024 |magazine=Time}}</ref>

The [[chainsaw]] has become an enduring and popular symbol associated with Milei<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-10-20 |title=A man, a plan, a chainsaw: How a power tool took center stage in Argentina's presidential race |url=https://apnews.com/article/milei-argentina-chainsaw-fed35a37c6137b951e4adada3d866436 |access-date=2024-01-02 |website=AP News |language=en |archive-date=28 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231228125418/https://apnews.com/article/milei-argentina-chainsaw-fed35a37c6137b951e4adada3d866436 |url-status=live}}</ref> (he has been called the "chainsaw candidate"<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sarmenti |first=Stefano Pozzebon,Ivan Perez |date=2023-10-01 |title=The 'chainsaw' candidate challenging Argentina's left and right |url=https://www.cnn.com/2023/10/01/americas/chainsaw-candidate-argentina-javier-milei-hnk-intl/index.html |access-date=2024-01-02 |website=CNN |language=en |archive-date=12 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231212061835/https://www.cnn.com/2023/10/01/americas/chainsaw-candidate-argentina-javier-milei-hnk-intl/index.html |url-status=live}}</ref>), specifically symbolizing his "cutting" of regulations, bureaucracy, and [[red tape]] in Argentina.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hall |first=Katarina |date=2023-12-29 |title=Milei brings his chainsaw to Argentina's regulatory state |url=https://reason.com/2023/12/29/milei-brings-his-chainsaw-to-argentinas-regulatory-state/ |access-date=2023-12-31 |website=Reason.com |language=en-US |archive-date=31 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231231203608/https://reason.com/2023/12/29/milei-brings-his-chainsaw-to-argentinas-regulatory-state/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Some commentators have called Milei's economic policy of cutting regulations "chainsaw economics".<ref>{{Cite news |last=Wallace |first=Tim |date=2023-12-13 |title=Why Javier Milei's chainsaw economics won IMF's approval when Trussonomics didn't |language=en-GB |work=The Telegraph |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/business/2023/12/13/javier-milei-argentina-shock-therapy-devaluing-peso/ |access-date=2024-01-02 |issn=0307-1235 |archive-date=2 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240102133922/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/business/2023/12/13/javier-milei-argentina-shock-therapy-devaluing-peso/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Milei's supporters often carry chainsaws at rallies, symbolizing "his promise to cut down the size of the state".<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-12-29 |title=Chainsaw at Work |url=https://www.thestatesman.com/opinion/chainsaw-at-work-1503254174.html |access-date=2024-01-02 |website=The Statesman |language=en |archive-date=2 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240102133922/https://www.thestatesman.com/opinion/chainsaw-at-work-1503254174.html |url-status=live}}</ref> Milei is also well known for his phrase "[[¡Viva la libertad, carajo!]]", which is uttered most especially at the end of various speeches given by him.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-11-22 |title=¡Viva la libertad, carajo!, por Daniel Capó |url=https://theobjective.com/elsubjetivo/opinion/2023-11-22/viva-libertad-carajo/ |access-date=2024-05-29 |website=THE OBJECTIVE |language=es}}</ref>

==Personal life==
[[File:Milei inicia en Nueva York su primera visita a EEUU como presidente electo de Argentina.png|thumb|Milei (center) praying in the grave of [[Menachem Mendel Schneerson]] on 27 November 2023]]
Milei is unmarried and said that, if elected president, he would have his sister take the role of [[First Lady of Argentina]].<ref name="Dadouch 2023">{{cite news |last=Dadouch |first=Sarah |date=14 August 2023 |title=Who is Javier Milei, Argentina's right-wing presidential front-runner |newspaper=The Washington Post |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2023/08/14/javier-milei-argentina-presidential-election |url-status=live |access-date=1 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230901190945/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2023/08/14/javier-milei-argentina-presidential-election |archive-date=1 September 2023 |issn=2641-9599}}</ref> In August 2023, Milei announced that he was dating actress [[Fátima Flórez]].<ref>{{cite web |date=21 August 2023 |title=Romance entre Javier Milei y Fátima Flórez: la actriz y el político confirmaron la relación |url=https://www.clarin.com/fama/rumores-romance-javier-milei-fatima-florez_0_OfJASGZ5UH.html |access-date=30 August 2023 |website=Clarín |language=es |archive-date=25 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230825114428/https://www.clarin.com/fama/rumores-romance-javier-milei-fatima-florez_0_OfJASGZ5UH.html |url-status=live}}</ref> Previously, he dated singer {{ill|Daniela Mori|lt=Daniela Mori|es}}.<ref>{{cite web |date=14 August 2023 |title=La alegría de la cantante Daniela, ex de Javier Milei, por la buena elección del libertario |url=https://www.clarin.com/fama/alegria-cantante-daniela-ex-javier-milei-buena-eleccion-libertario_0_yosOTIjTYD.html |access-date=30 August 2023 |website=Clarín |language=es |archive-date=30 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230830195750/https://www.clarin.com/fama/alegria-cantante-daniela-ex-javier-milei-buena-eleccion-libertario_0_yosOTIjTYD.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

While raised [[Catholic]],<ref>{{cite tweet |last=Milei |first=Javier |user=JMilei |date=5 October 2017 |number=915941489125003265 |title=Disculpame. Yo soy católico. Y en mis valores la violencia y el robo está mal. Será un problema tuyo si avalás el robo y recorte de libertad|<!--trans-title=I'm sorry, I'm a Catholic, and in my values violence and robbery are wrong. It's your problem if you endorse robbery and liberties cutbacks|-->language=es |access-date=15 August 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=29 October 2021 |title=Milei, el libertario que provoca a los cristianos |url=https://www.letrap.com.ar/nota/2021-10-29-13-58-0-milei-el-libertario-que-provoca-a-los-cristianos |access-date=27 August 2023 |website=LetraP |language=es |archive-date=27 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230827170758/https://www.letrap.com.ar/nota/2021-10-29-13-58-0-milei-el-libertario-que-provoca-a-los-cristianos |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Gillespie & Tobias 2023">{{cite news |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-11-27/milei-s-conversion-to-judaism-seals-pro-israel-push-by-argentina |title=Milei's Conversion to Judaism Seals Pro-Israel Push by Argentina |last1=Gillespie |first1=Patrick |last2=Tobias |first2=Manuela |date=27 November 2023 |work=Bloomberg News |access-date=27 November 2023 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20231127233058/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-11-27/milei-s-conversion-to-judaism-seals-pro-israel-push-by-argentina |archive-date=27 November 2023}}</ref> Milei has been critical of the [[Catholic Church]] under [[Pope Francis]],<ref>{{cite news |last=Goñi |first=Uki |date=27 August 2023 |title=The 'false prophet' v the pope: Argentina faces clash of ideologies in election |work=The Observer<!--The Guardian--> |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/27/the-false-prophet-v-the-pope-argentina-faces-clash-of-ideologies-in-election |access-date=27 August 2023 |issn=0029-7712 |archive-date=27 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230827073826/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/27/the-false-prophet-v-the-pope-argentina-faces-clash-of-ideologies-in-election |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Cholakian Herrera |first1=Lucía |last2=Nicas |first2=Jack |date=16 October 2023 |title=He Called the Pope a 'Filthy Leftist.' Now He Wants to Be President |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2023/10/16/world/americas/javier-milei-pope-francis-argentina-election.html |access-date=28 November 2023 |issn=1553-8095 |archive-date=22 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231122022050/https://www.nytimes.com/2023/10/16/world/americas/javier-milei-pope-francis-argentina-election.html |url-status=live}}</ref> and his disparaging comments about Francis attracted criticism from Catholics.<ref>{{cite web |last=Villarreal |first=Guillermo |date=6 May 2022 |title=Milei, un católico flojo de papeles que se arma con El Reino evangélico |url=https://www.letrap.com.ar/nota/2022-5-6-15-12-0-milei-un-catolico-flojo-de-papeles-que-se-arma-con-el-reino-evangelico |access-date=27 August 2023 |website=LetraP |language=es |archive-date=27 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230827170758/https://www.letrap.com.ar/nota/2022-5-6-15-12-0-milei-un-catolico-flojo-de-papeles-que-se-arma-con-el-reino-evangelico |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=24 August 2023 |title=La iglesia católica vs. Milei: 'Llega un momento donde tenemos que decir 'No' |url=https://www.newsweek.com.ar/politica/la-iglesia-catolica-vs-milei-llega-un-momento-donde-tenemos-que-decir-no |access-date=27 August 2023 |website=Newsweek Argentina |language=es |archive-date=27 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230827170759/https://www.newsweek.com.ar/politica/la-iglesia-catolica-vs-milei-llega-un-momento-donde-tenemos-que-decir-no/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Milei also reads the [[Torah]] daily and has visited the grave of Orthodox rabbi [[Menachem Mendel Schneerson]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Isaac |first=David |date=21 November 2023 |title=Argentina's first 'Jewish' president? Milei wins decisive victory |url=https://www.jns.org/argentinas-first-jewish-president-milei-wins-decisive-victory/ |access-date=21 November 2023 |website=Jewish News Syndicate |archive-date=21 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231121180626/https://www.jns.org/argentinas-first-jewish-president-milei-wins-decisive-victory/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=20 November 2023 |title=Argentina's New Eclectic President Has Visited the Rebbe's Ohel |url=https://collive.com/argentinas-new-eclectic-president-has-visited-the-rebbes-ohel/ |access-date=21 November 2023 |website=COLlive |archive-date=21 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231121020728/https://collive.com/argentinas-new-eclectic-president-has-visited-the-rebbes-ohel/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Miller |first=Leila |date=9 December 2023 |title=In Catholic Argentina, President Javier Milei has a rabbi — and likes talking about it |url=https://www.latimes.com/world-nation/story/2023-12-09/la-fg-milei-jewish |access-date=11 December 2023 |work=Los Angeles Times |archive-date=11 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231211011349/https://www.latimes.com/world-nation/story/2023-12-09/la-fg-milei-jewish |url-status=live}}</ref> Before November 2023, Milei said he had contemplated [[converting to Judaism]] but that observing the [[Jewish Sabbath]] could pose challenges if he became president.<ref name="Sivak 2023"/><ref>{{Cite web |date=20 November 2023 |title=Newly elected Argentine president Javier Milei says he will visit Israel in advance of inauguration |url=https://www.algemeiner.com/2023/11/20/newly-elected-argentine-president-javier-milei-says-he-will-visit-israel-advance-inauguration/ |access-date=21 November 2023 |first=Ben |last=Cohen |website=Algemeiner Journal |archive-date=20 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231120182025/https://www.algemeiner.com/2023/11/20/newly-elected-argentine-president-javier-milei-says-he-will-visit-israel-advance-inauguration/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=20 November 2023 |title=Argentina's New President Spoke About the Rebbe, Visited Ohel |website=Anash |url=https://anash.org/argentinas-new-president-spoke-about-the-rebbe-visited-ohel/ |access-date=21 November 2023 |archive-date=20 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231120181838/https://anash.org/argentinas-new-president-spoke-about-the-rebbe-visited-ohel/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Upon being elected president, it was reported that Milei intended to convert to Judaism.<ref name="Gillespie & Tobias 2023" />

Milei owns five [[English Mastiff]]s, with the progenitor being [[Conan (Javier Milei's dog)|Conan]], who died in 2017 after suffering from [[spinal cancer]].<ref name="iProfesional 2023"/><ref name="González 2023"/><ref name="El Doce 2023">{{cite web |date=15 August 2023 |title=Conan, el perro cordobés de Milei que murió y fue clonado por miles de dólares |url=https://eldoce.tv/curioso/conan-perro-cordobes-javier-milei-murio-fue-clonado-miles-dolares_153231 |access-date=25 August 2023 |website=El Doce<!--ElDoce.tv--> |language=es |archive-date=22 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230822145324/https://eldoce.tv/curioso/conan-perro-cordobes-javier-milei-murio-fue-clonado-miles-dolares_153231 |url-status=live}}</ref> He considers Conan his son and has named four of Conan's six [[Cloning|clones]], including one named after the original and another named Angelito,<ref>{{cite web |date=5 July 2023 |title=Revelan los secretos místicos de Javier Milei: esoterismo, la 'misión' de dios y charlas con su perro muerto |url=https://www.ambito.com/politica/revelan-los-secretos-misticos-javier-milei-esoterismo-la-mision-dios-y-charlas-su-perro-muerto-n5762291 |access-date=25 August 2023 |website=Ámbito |archive-date=16 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230816212533/https://www.ambito.com/politica/revelan-los-secretos-misticos-javier-milei-esoterismo-la-mision-dios-y-charlas-su-perro-muerto-n5762291 |url-status=live}}</ref> Milton (in honor of [[Milton Friedman]]), Murray (in honor of [[Murray Rothbard]]), Robert, and Lucas (both named after [[Robert Lucas Jr.]]).<ref>{{cite web |date=20 August 2018 |title=Milei presentó a su 'hijo' Conan y a sus 'nietos' de cuatro patas en Infama Recargado |url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/entertainment/celebrity/milei-present%C3%B3-a-su-hijo-conan-y-a-sus-nietos-de-cuatro-patas-en-infama-recargado/ar-BBM9ekN?li=AAggpOc&%25252525252525253Bocid=mailsignout |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190328064128/https://www.msn.com/en-us/entertainment/celebrity/milei-present%C3%B3-a-su-hijo-conan-y-a-sus-nietos-de-cuatro-patas-en-infama-recargado/ar-BBM9ekN?li=AAggpOc&%25252525252525253Bocid=mailsignout |archive-date=28 March 2019 |access-date=2 December 2018 |website=América TV |language=es |via=MSN}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Portes |first=Ignacio |date=9 July 2023 |title=Argentina's media takes aim at Milei's craziest side |url=https://brazilian.report/latin-america/2023/07/09/argentina-media-attack-milei |access-date=14 August 2023 |website=The Brazilian Report |archive-date=10 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230710144034/https://brazilian.report/latin-america/2023/07/09/argentina-media-attack-milei/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Milei said that he cloned Conan because he understands cloning as "a way of approaching eternity".<ref name="El Doce 2023"/> To do this, he went to a clinic in the United States; the process cost him about $50,000.<ref name="El Doce 2023"/> He has called his dogs his "four-legged children" and thanked them after his electoral win.<ref name="Viriglio 2023"/><ref>{{cite news |last=Nicas |first=Jack |date=19 October 2023 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2023/10/19/world/americas/argentina-election-javier-milei.html |title=The 5 Clones in Argentina's Election |work=The New York Times |issn=1553-8095 |access-date=28 November 2023 |archive-date=24 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231124161038/https://www.nytimes.com/2023/10/19/world/americas/argentina-election-javier-milei.html |url-status=live}}</ref> Milei has also stated that he has [[ornithophobia]].<ref>{{Cite AV media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z1W2QcjzaHo |title=Milei at the Buenos Aires World Economic Forum – October 23, 2024 – Translated with AI |date=2024-10-26 |last=Voices Of Freedom |access-date=2024-11-10 |via=YouTube}}</ref>

Milei is an avid fan of [[Association football|association football.]] Albeit having played for [[Chacarita Juniors]] in his early adulthood, Milei has stated to be a supporter of [[Boca Juniors|Boca Juniors;]] in a 2024 interview with [[Radio Mitre|Radio Mitre,]] Milei said, "I am a member and fan of Boca. If investment groups come and put a fortune for us to win all the time, where do I sign?"<ref>{{Cite web |last=Olé |first=Diario Deportivo |date=2024-01-07 |title=Los clubes argentinos que quiere comprar el Chelsea, según Milei |url=https://www.ole.com.ar/informacion-general/clubes-argentinos-quiere-comprar-chelsea-milei_0_vHC0Z0OMGI.html |access-date=2024-12-27 |website=Olé |language=es-AR}}</ref> However, he has expressed criticism of the presidency of [[Juan Román Riquelme]] at the club since 2023, stating that his "management at Boca is a disaster" and referred to Riquelme as "a [[Kirchnerism|Kirchnerist]] running the club."<ref>{{Cite web |title=Javier Milei volvió a cargar contra Román Riquelme: “Su gestión en Boca es un desastre” |url=https://www.ambito.com/deportes/javier-milei-volvio-cargar-contra-roman-riquelme-su-gestion-boca-es-un-desastre-n6081780 |access-date=2024-12-27 |website=www.ambito.com}}</ref>

In December 2024, Milei applied for and was granted [[Italian nationality law|Italian citizenship]] via ''[[jus sanguinis]]'' under the government of Prime Minister [[Giorgia Meloni]], which was met with public criticism.<ref>{{Cite web |date=13 December 2024 |title=The government has granted Italian citizenship to Javier Milei |url=https://www.ilpost.it/2024/12/13/javier-milei-cittadinanza-italiana-meloni/ |access-date=13 December 2024 |website=IL Post |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=2024-12-13 |title=Argentina's president Javier Milei given Italian citizenship, sparking outrage |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2024/dec/13/javier-milei-argentina-italian-citizenship |access-date=2024-12-19 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077 |agency=Reuters}}</ref>

